ct\" target=\"_blank\">新研究报告</a>称：<a name=\"OLE_LINK4\"></a><a name=\"OLE_LINK3\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶</span></a>（俗称“帝王蝶”）可以利用药用植物治愈自身及其后代的疾病。</span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">该疾病由一种叫做</span><i><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">Ophryocystis elektroscirrha</span></i><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">的原生动物寄生虫引发。这种寄生虫侵入毛毛虫的肠道，一直存活到毛毛虫化茧成蝶。</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><a href=\"http://esciencecommons.blogspot.com/2010/09/do-monarch-butterflies-use-drugs.html\" target=\"_blank\">eScience Commons</a></span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">的项目负责人<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Jaap de Roode</span>今天说：“幼虫的食物是乳草，事实证明一些乳草可以降低黑脉金斑蝶感染寄生虫的几率。我们还发现受感染的雌性蝴蝶喜欢在一些能使它们后代少生病的植物上产卵，这说明黑脉金斑蝶用药治疗后代的能力得到了进化。</span></p>   <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">（图片：</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">Jaap deRoode and Lisa Sharling</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">摄</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">）<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶毛毛虫<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151037_36566.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left:54.0pt;text-indent:-21.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:0;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;font-family:wingdings;mso-fareast-font-family:wingdings;mso-bidi-font-family:wingdings;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-bidi-font-style:italic;\"><span style=\"mso-list:ignore;\"><span style=\"font:7.0pt \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶成虫<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151056_21888.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">埃默里大学（<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Emory University</span>）生物学助理教授</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">De Roode</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">说：“我们认为在证明动物使用药物这方面，我们的实验提供了迄今为止最好的证据。”<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151025_36615.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-bidi-font-family:宋体;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-bidi-font-style:italic;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:'sans serif', tahoma, verdana, helvetica;line-height:25px;font-size:14px;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:52px;font-size:16px;\">J</span>aap de Rooodez</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">在《发现新闻》频道一段<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/EmoryUniversity#p/u/0/6Mjs39mF17I\" target=\"_blank\">视频</a>中探讨了他的最新调查结果，以前我们也谈及过这个话题，不过是针对其他物种。例如蜘蛛猴，据称它们发现了一种<a href=\"http://dsc.discovery.com/news/2009/07/31/spider-monkey-scratcher.html\" target=\"_blank\">药用的身体抓扒工具</a>。但有关动物自我医疗这方面的研究还是相对较少。</span></span></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><br /> </span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">受寄生虫感染奄奄一息的黑脉金斑蝶<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151042_18840.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:45.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶很漂亮，但是却处在食物链的底端。这样的生物表现出来的这种行为便增加了人们几分兴趣。“并且这种行为是跨代的，”</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">de Roode</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">实验室的一位博士后研究员</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Thierry Lefevre</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">说，“母亲表现这样的行为，只会让她的后代受益。”</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;\"><o></o></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:45.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">非人类物种作出的有关健康的选择将来也可能会让我们人类受益。比如像</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Mark Hunter</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">这样的化学生态学家一直在致力于乳草的研究，以确定其药用价值。</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;\"><o></o></span></p> <p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/169844/142487?from=rss_related\">智利被困矿工被曝在被困初期曾发生内讧</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/111225/142476?from=rss_related\">五十部最适合家庭观看的电影之--《杀死一只知更鸟》</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/177576/142362?from=rss_related\">科学家公布DNA检测结果以促进建立世界性的DNA数据库</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/180478/142155?from=rss_related\">汽车声音的未来</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/105279/142097?from=rss_related\">欧洲航天局追查非法无线电发射台 保护卫星通信安全</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804557/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804557/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804557/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505" (19636 5683) old 1 nil nil ((title nil "蝴蝶利用植物进行自我药疗") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T08:02:59+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T08:02:59+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T08:02:59+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142505") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "明日之梯") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/144621")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.discovery.com/animals/butterflies-cure-themselves-of-disease-by-using-medicinal-plants.html\">【Discovery News】Butterflies Cure Themselves with Plants</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/144621\">明日之梯</a></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">《生态学学报》杂志上发表的一份<a href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1461-0248.2010.01537.x/abstract\" target=\"_blank\">新研究报告</a>称：<a name=\"OLE_LINK4\"></a><a name=\"OLE_LINK3\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶</span></a>（俗称“帝王蝶”）可以利用药用植物治愈自身及其后代的疾病。</span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">该疾病由一种叫做</span><i><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">Ophryocystis elektroscirrha</span></i><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">的原生动物寄生虫引发。这种寄生虫侵入毛毛虫的肠道，一直存活到毛毛虫化茧成蝶。</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><a href=\"http://esciencecommons.blogspot.com/2010/09/do-monarch-butterflies-use-drugs.html\" target=\"_blank\">eScience Commons</a></span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">的项目负责人<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Jaap de Roode</span>今天说：“幼虫的食物是乳草，事实证明一些乳草可以降低黑脉金斑蝶感染寄生虫的几率。我们还发现受感染的雌性蝴蝶喜欢在一些能使它们后代少生病的植物上产卵，这说明黑脉金斑蝶用药治疗后代的能力得到了进化。</span></p>   <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">（图片：</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">Jaap deRoode and Lisa Sharling</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">摄</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">）<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶毛毛虫<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151037_36566.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left:54.0pt;text-indent:-21.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:0;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;font-family:wingdings;mso-fareast-font-family:wingdings;mso-bidi-font-family:wingdings;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-bidi-font-style:italic;\"><span style=\"mso-list:ignore;\"><span style=\"font:7.0pt \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶成虫<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151056_21888.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">埃默里大学（<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Emory University</span>）生物学助理教授</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">De Roode</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">说：“我们认为在证明动物使用药物这方面，我们的实验提供了迄今为止最好的证据。”<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151025_36615.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-bidi-font-family:宋体;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-bidi-font-style:italic;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:'sans serif', tahoma, verdana, helvetica;line-height:25px;font-size:14px;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:52px;font-size:16px;\">J</span>aap de Rooodez</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">在《发现新闻》频道一段<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/EmoryUniversity#p/u/0/6Mjs39mF17I\" target=\"_blank\">视频</a>中探讨了他的最新调查结果，以前我们也谈及过这个话题，不过是针对其他物种。例如蜘蛛猴，据称它们发现了一种<a href=\"http://dsc.discovery.com/news/2009/07/31/spider-monkey-scratcher.html\" target=\"_blank\">药用的身体抓扒工具</a>。但有关动物自我医疗这方面的研究还是相对较少。</span></span></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><br /> </span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">受寄生虫感染奄奄一息的黑脉金斑蝶<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151042_18840.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:45.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶很漂亮，但是却处在食物链的底端。这样的生物表现出来的这种行为便增加了人们几分兴趣。“并且这种行为是跨代的，”</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">de Roode</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">实验室的一位博士后研究员</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Thierry Lefevre</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">说，“母亲表现这样的行为，只会让她的后代受益。”</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;\"><o></o></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:45.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">非人类物种作出的有关健康的选择将来也可能会让我们人类受益。比如像</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Mark Hunter</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">这样的化学生态学家一直在致力于乳草的研究，以确定其药用价值。</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;\"><o></o></span></p> <p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/169844/142487?from=rss_related\">智利被困矿工被曝在被困初期曾发生内讧</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/111225/142476?from=rss_related\">五十部最适合家庭观看的电影之--《杀死一只知更鸟》</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/177576/142362?from=rss_related\">科学家公布DNA检测结果以促进建立世界性的DNA数据库</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/180478/142155?from=rss_related\">汽车声音的未来</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/105279/142097?from=rss_related\">欧洲航天局追查非法无线电发射台 保护卫星通信安全</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.discovery.com/animals/butterflies-cure-themselves-of-disease-by-using-medicinal-plants.html\">【Discovery News】Butterflies Cure Themselves with Plants</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/144621\">明日之梯</a></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">《生态学学报》杂志上发表的一份<a href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1461-0248.2010.01537.x/abstract\" target=\"_blank\">新研究报告</a>称：<a name=\"OLE_LINK4\"></a><a name=\"OLE_LINK3\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶</span></a>（俗称“帝王蝶”）可以利用药用植物治愈自身及其后代的疾病。</span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">该疾病由一种叫做</span><i><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">Ophryocystis elektroscirrha</span></i><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">的原生动物寄生虫引发。这种寄生虫侵入毛毛虫的肠道，一直存活到毛毛虫化茧成蝶。</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><a href=\"http://esciencecommons.blogspot.com/2010/09/do-monarch-butterflies-use-drugs.html\" target=\"_blank\">eScience Commons</a></span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">的项目负责人<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Jaap de Roode</span>今天说：“幼虫的食物是乳草，事实证明一些乳草可以降低黑脉金斑蝶感染寄生虫的几率。我们还发现受感染的雌性蝴蝶喜欢在一些能使它们后代少生病的植物上产卵，这说明黑脉金斑蝶用药治疗后代的能力得到了进化。</span></p>   <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">（图片：</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">Jaap deRoode and Lisa Sharling</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">摄</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">）<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶毛毛虫<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151037_36566.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left:54.0pt;text-indent:-21.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:0;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;font-family:wingdings;mso-fareast-font-family:wingdings;mso-bidi-font-family:wingdings;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-bidi-font-style:italic;\"><span style=\"mso-list:ignore;\"><span style=\"font:7.0pt \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶成虫<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151056_21888.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">埃默里大学（<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Emory University</span>）生物学助理教授</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">De Roode</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">说：“我们认为在证明动物使用药物这方面，我们的实验提供了迄今为止最好的证据。”<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151025_36615.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-bidi-font-family:宋体;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-bidi-font-style:italic;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:'sans serif', tahoma, verdana, helvetica;line-height:25px;font-size:14px;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:52px;font-size:16px;\">J</span>aap de Rooodez</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">在《发现新闻》频道一段<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/EmoryUniversity#p/u/0/6Mjs39mF17I\" target=\"_blank\">视频</a>中探讨了他的最新调查结果，以前我们也谈及过这个话题，不过是针对其他物种。例如蜘蛛猴，据称它们发现了一种<a href=\"http://dsc.discovery.com/news/2009/07/31/spider-monkey-scratcher.html\" target=\"_blank\">药用的身体抓扒工具</a>。但有关动物自我医疗这方面的研究还是相对较少。</span></span></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\"><br /> </span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:33.0pt;mso-char-indent-count:1.5;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">受寄生虫感染奄奄一息的黑脉金斑蝶<span lang=\"EN-US\"><o></o></span></span></p>  <p><img src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151042_18840.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </p> &nbsp;&nbsp;<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:45.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">黑脉金斑蝶很漂亮，但是却处在食物链的底端。这样的生物表现出来的这种行为便增加了人们几分兴趣。“并且这种行为是跨代的，”</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">de Roode</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">实验室的一位博士后研究员</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Thierry Lefevre</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">说，“母亲表现这样的行为，只会让她的后代受益。”</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;\"><o></o></span></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent:45.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">非人类物种作出的有关健康的选择将来也可能会让我们人类受益。比如像</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:16px;\">Mark Hunter</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;font-size:16px;\">这样的化学生态学家一直在致力于乳草的研究，以确定其药用价值。</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:22.0pt;\"><o></o></span></p> <p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/169844/142487?from=rss_related\">智利被困矿工被曝在被困初期曾发生内讧</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/111225/142476?from=rss_related\">五十部最适合家庭观看的电影之--《杀死一只知更鸟》</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/177576/142362?from=rss_related\">科学家公布DNA检测结果以促进建立世界性的DNA数据库</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/180478/142155?from=rss_related\">汽车声音的未来</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/105279/142097?from=rss_related\">欧洲航天局追查非法无线电发射台 保护卫星通信安全</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804557/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804557/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804557/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>") (pubDate nil "Tue, 12 Oct 2010 16:02:59 +0800") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142505") (dc:creator nil "明日之梯") (fs:srclink nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/144621/142505") (fs:srcfeed nil "http://www.yeeyan.org/feed/category/310") (fs:itemid nil "feedsky/yeeyan-science/~8024232/422804557/5034837"))) ("鲸鱼粪便可补充海水养分" "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=130437080\">Whales Help Fertilize Ocean With Floating Dung</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/154469\">gladysvii</a></p><p>作者：乔伊·帕卡</p> <p>2010-10-11</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151033_57542.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>凯克·卡尔沃/AP<br /> 一头矮人小须鲸在大堡礁附近游泳。科学家称鲸鱼粪便可供海面附近的鱼类食用。<br /> </p> <p>鲸鱼即将得到一批新的支持者。谈论到海洋问题，它们总是很热门，而根据最新研究，渔民也可能喊起“拯救鲸鱼”的口号。</p> <p>原因来自海藻。海藻包括小到单细胞有机体、大到巨型褐藻的多种类型植物，有些海藻生长于海面附近，依赖氮元素成长。</p> <p>“它们也需要其他营养，但就我们观察，其限制营养素通常是氮元素，”佛蒙特大学的环保生物学家乔伊·罗曼说：“那是海藻需求最大的营养素。”</p> <p>罗曼说，一旦海藻缺乏氮元素，它们终将死去，并带着氮沉入海底。有时鱼吃海藻，然后排便，氮也就随鱼类的粪便沉了下去。</p> <p>“另一方面，鲸鱼通常在深海觅食，”罗曼说：“它们在深水层吃东西，在海面附近排便。”</p> <p>罗曼怎么知道鲸鱼在海面排便？这是他下海观察所得。</p> <p>“无论鲸鱼何时在海面排便，我们都跟着它，并收集其粪便，”他说。</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151004_87922.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>这张图显示了鲸鱼粪便中的养分在海洋生态系统中是如何转移的。（图片由佛特蒙大学提供）</p> <p><strong>漂浮的粪便</strong></p> <p>鲸鱼粪便与其他鱼类粪便的区别在于，鲸鱼粪便会漂浮在海面上，或者，至少停留在海面附近。</p> <p>这点很重要，因为当罗曼把鲸鱼粪便带回他的实验室后，他发现里面富含氮元素。这样一来，这些沉入海底的养分，又被鲸鱼逮到了海面上。</p> <p>“所以，本质上，通过排便，鲸鱼为他们赖以生存的海洋补充了养分，”他说。</p> <p>不仅海藻的数量因此增加，鱼类也变多了，因为海藻是鱼的食物。</p> <p><strong>无私的鲸鱼</strong></p> <p>罗曼称，鲸鱼可供养给鱼类朋友，这很令人惊讶。</p> <p>“通常，鲸鱼被看做是食物的竞争者，”他说：“但现在，我们发现其实鲸鱼也会提供食物。”</p> <p>在此之前，已有科学家怀疑鲸鱼和其他大型鱼类，能够把海水中某个地方的养分运送到另一个地方。</p> <p>“关键问题在于，鲸鱼粪便的确增加了海水中的氮，还是仅仅加快了氮循环的速度？”缅因大学研究院的科学家安德鲁·珀欣说。</p> <p>暴风骤雨亦可将海底养分移动到海面，鲸鱼的工作与之区别何在，尚未为人所知。</p> <p>“这很像一个会计问题，”珀欣说：“你是在当地从事金钱贸易，还是真的创造了GDP的增长?”</p> <p>当然我们在此谈论的不是经济问题，而是肥料——或养分，从理论上讲。珀欣说，罗曼的研究会使科学家们更关注海洋生态系统中，大型海洋生物扮演的角色。</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/140673?from=rss_related\">海洋生物的‘人口普查’</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/140680?from=rss_related\">【卫报图集】英国南极调查发现新物种</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/92797/140505?from=rss_related\">捕鲸猎杀大型鱼类改变了海洋吸存碳的能力</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/92797/140427?from=rss_related\">日益酸化的海洋将使海洋生物处于万劫不复的悲惨境地</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/138606?from=rss_related\">【卫报】图集：最后的海上游牧部落</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804561/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804561/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804561/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420" (19636 2618) old 2 nil nil ((title nil "鲸鱼粪便可补充海水养分") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T07:11:54+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T07:11:54+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T07:11:54+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142420") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "gladysvii") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/154469")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=130437080\">Whales Help Fertilize Ocean With Floating Dung</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/154469\">gladysvii</a></p><p>作者：乔伊·帕卡</p> <p>2010-10-11</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151033_57542.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>凯克·卡尔沃/AP<br /> 一头矮人小须鲸在大堡礁附近游泳。科学家称鲸鱼粪便可供海面附近的鱼类食用。<br /> </p> <p>鲸鱼即将得到一批新的支持者。谈论到海洋问题，它们总是很热门，而根据最新研究，渔民也可能喊起“拯救鲸鱼”的口号。</p> <p>原因来自海藻。海藻包括小到单细胞有机体、大到巨型褐藻的多种类型植物，有些海藻生长于海面附近，依赖氮元素成长。</p> <p>“它们也需要其他营养，但就我们观察，其限制营养素通常是氮元素，”佛蒙特大学的环保生物学家乔伊·罗曼说：“那是海藻需求最大的营养素。”</p> <p>罗曼说，一旦海藻缺乏氮元素，它们终将死去，并带着氮沉入海底。有时鱼吃海藻，然后排便，氮也就随鱼类的粪便沉了下去。</p> <p>“另一方面，鲸鱼通常在深海觅食，”罗曼说：“它们在深水层吃东西，在海面附近排便。”</p> <p>罗曼怎么知道鲸鱼在海面排便？这是他下海观察所得。</p> <p>“无论鲸鱼何时在海面排便，我们都跟着它，并收集其粪便，”他说。</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151004_87922.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>这张图显示了鲸鱼粪便中的养分在海洋生态系统中是如何转移的。（图片由佛特蒙大学提供）</p> <p><strong>漂浮的粪便</strong></p> <p>鲸鱼粪便与其他鱼类粪便的区别在于，鲸鱼粪便会漂浮在海面上，或者，至少停留在海面附近。</p> <p>这点很重要，因为当罗曼把鲸鱼粪便带回他的实验室后，他发现里面富含氮元素。这样一来，这些沉入海底的养分，又被鲸鱼逮到了海面上。</p> <p>“所以，本质上，通过排便，鲸鱼为他们赖以生存的海洋补充了养分，”他说。</p> <p>不仅海藻的数量因此增加，鱼类也变多了，因为海藻是鱼的食物。</p> <p><strong>无私的鲸鱼</strong></p> <p>罗曼称，鲸鱼可供养给鱼类朋友，这很令人惊讶。</p> <p>“通常，鲸鱼被看做是食物的竞争者，”他说：“但现在，我们发现其实鲸鱼也会提供食物。”</p> <p>在此之前，已有科学家怀疑鲸鱼和其他大型鱼类，能够把海水中某个地方的养分运送到另一个地方。</p> <p>“关键问题在于，鲸鱼粪便的确增加了海水中的氮，还是仅仅加快了氮循环的速度？”缅因大学研究院的科学家安德鲁·珀欣说。</p> <p>暴风骤雨亦可将海底养分移动到海面，鲸鱼的工作与之区别何在，尚未为人所知。</p> <p>“这很像一个会计问题，”珀欣说：“你是在当地从事金钱贸易，还是真的创造了GDP的增长?”</p> <p>当然我们在此谈论的不是经济问题，而是肥料——或养分，从理论上讲。珀欣说，罗曼的研究会使科学家们更关注海洋生态系统中，大型海洋生物扮演的角色。</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/140673?from=rss_related\">海洋生物的‘人口普查’</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/140680?from=rss_related\">【卫报图集】英国南极调查发现新物种</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/92797/140505?from=rss_related\">捕鲸猎杀大型鱼类改变了海洋吸存碳的能力</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/92797/140427?from=rss_related\">日益酸化的海洋将使海洋生物处于万劫不复的悲惨境地</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/138606?from=rss_related\">【卫报】图集：最后的海上游牧部落</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=130437080\">Whales Help Fertilize Ocean With Floating Dung</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/154469\">gladysvii</a></p><p>作者：乔伊·帕卡</p> <p>2010-10-11</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151033_57542.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>凯克·卡尔沃/AP<br /> 一头矮人小须鲸在大堡礁附近游泳。科学家称鲸鱼粪便可供海面附近的鱼类食用。<br /> </p> <p>鲸鱼即将得到一批新的支持者。谈论到海洋问题，它们总是很热门，而根据最新研究，渔民也可能喊起“拯救鲸鱼”的口号。</p> <p>原因来自海藻。海藻包括小到单细胞有机体、大到巨型褐藻的多种类型植物，有些海藻生长于海面附近，依赖氮元素成长。</p> <p>“它们也需要其他营养，但就我们观察，其限制营养素通常是氮元素，”佛蒙特大学的环保生物学家乔伊·罗曼说：“那是海藻需求最大的营养素。”</p> <p>罗曼说，一旦海藻缺乏氮元素，它们终将死去，并带着氮沉入海底。有时鱼吃海藻，然后排便，氮也就随鱼类的粪便沉了下去。</p> <p>“另一方面，鲸鱼通常在深海觅食，”罗曼说：“它们在深水层吃东西，在海面附近排便。”</p> <p>罗曼怎么知道鲸鱼在海面排便？这是他下海观察所得。</p> <p>“无论鲸鱼何时在海面排便，我们都跟着它，并收集其粪便，”他说。</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012151004_87922.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>这张图显示了鲸鱼粪便中的养分在海洋生态系统中是如何转移的。（图片由佛特蒙大学提供）</p> <p><strong>漂浮的粪便</strong></p> <p>鲸鱼粪便与其他鱼类粪便的区别在于，鲸鱼粪便会漂浮在海面上，或者，至少停留在海面附近。</p> <p>这点很重要，因为当罗曼把鲸鱼粪便带回他的实验室后，他发现里面富含氮元素。这样一来，这些沉入海底的养分，又被鲸鱼逮到了海面上。</p> <p>“所以，本质上，通过排便，鲸鱼为他们赖以生存的海洋补充了养分，”他说。</p> <p>不仅海藻的数量因此增加，鱼类也变多了，因为海藻是鱼的食物。</p> <p><strong>无私的鲸鱼</strong></p> <p>罗曼称，鲸鱼可供养给鱼类朋友，这很令人惊讶。</p> <p>“通常，鲸鱼被看做是食物的竞争者，”他说：“但现在，我们发现其实鲸鱼也会提供食物。”</p> <p>在此之前，已有科学家怀疑鲸鱼和其他大型鱼类，能够把海水中某个地方的养分运送到另一个地方。</p> <p>“关键问题在于，鲸鱼粪便的确增加了海水中的氮，还是仅仅加快了氮循环的速度？”缅因大学研究院的科学家安德鲁·珀欣说。</p> <p>暴风骤雨亦可将海底养分移动到海面，鲸鱼的工作与之区别何在，尚未为人所知。</p> <p>“这很像一个会计问题，”珀欣说：“你是在当地从事金钱贸易，还是真的创造了GDP的增长?”</p> <p>当然我们在此谈论的不是经济问题，而是肥料——或养分，从理论上讲。珀欣说，罗曼的研究会使科学家们更关注海洋生态系统中，大型海洋生物扮演的角色。</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/140673?from=rss_related\">海洋生物的‘人口普查’</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/140680?from=rss_related\">【卫报图集】英国南极调查发现新物种</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/92797/140505?from=rss_related\">捕鲸猎杀大型鱼类改变了海洋吸存碳的能力</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/92797/140427?from=rss_related\">日益酸化的海洋将使海洋生物处于万劫不复的悲惨境地</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/95021/138606?from=rss_related\">【卫报】图集：最后的海上游牧部落</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804561/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804561/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804561/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>") (pubDate nil "Tue, 12 Oct 2010 15:11:54 +0800") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142420") (dc:creator nil "gladysvii") (fs:srclink nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/154469/142420") (fs:srcfeed nil "http://www.yeeyan.org/feed/category/310") (fs:itemid nil "feedsky/yeeyan-science/~8024232/422804561/5034837"))) ("北约高官警告称气候变化可能导致北极冲突" "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/oct/11/nato-conflict-arctic-resources\">Climate change could lead to Arctic conflict, warns senior Nato commander | Environment | guardiancouk</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/181261\">迈克尔</a></p><h1>北约高官警告气候变化可能导致北极冲突</h1> <p id=\"stand-first\" class=\"stand-first-alone\">美国海军上将在即将召开的环境安全会谈前警告称，全球变暖和世界各国对资源的争夺可能在北极地区引发新一轮“冷战”。</p> <p class=\"third-party-tool reddit\" sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"53\">&nbsp;</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"63\">詹姆斯·G·斯塔夫里蒂斯将军是欧洲盟军最高指挥官，他的这番言论是针对即将在周三召开的北冰洋环境安全启动会议。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"63\">俄罗斯将参加本次会谈。会谈将以研讨会的形式进行，北约希望与莫斯科建立对话机制以避免第二次冷战发生。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"64\">“目前为止，北极地区的所有争议都通过和平手段解决。但是气候变化将使这个地区自然资源更容易获取，竞争将会加剧，目前的平衡也将被打破，”斯塔夫里蒂斯将军表示。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"64\">这位美国海军上将确信军事力量将在这个地区扮演重要角色 - 但主要是协助专家们开展工作，而这些专家却由商业或其他利益集团驱动。</p> <p>他还补充称：“全球领导人应该评估各国对北极地区兴趣的升温及气候变化带来的广泛影响，同时共同努力确保北极是一个合作的地区 - 而不是一个竞争或冲突的地方</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"65\">斯塔夫里蒂斯将军的观点是通过英国白厅的《北冰洋环境安全：推动合作组织冲突》报告的前言中阐述自己的观点，该报告的作者是剑桥大学北冰洋地缘政治学项目负责人保罗·伯克曼教授。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"67\">会议由于北极地区冰盖迅速融化而变得非常紧迫，因为这将导致开采石油和其他矿藏更加容易。会议将在伯克曼教授所在的斯科特极地研究所举办。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"68\">最近数周，Cairn Energy公司公布其在格林兰附近海域返现数个石油和天然气点，同时政府将授予多个开采证书。俄罗斯与挪威也在英国石油公司墨西哥湾漏油事故的阴影下在各自的北部地区采取相似的行动。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"71\">俄罗斯总理弗拉基米尔·普京两周前在莫斯科举行的北极国际论坛上的发言涉及到了所谓的“共同责任”。他也注意到，冰盖融化为石油和其他矿藏的运输提供了直接通道，但北极是一个“合作与对话的地区”。</p> <p>贝克曼教授作为本次研讨会的主要组织者，得到了北约和平与安全科学项目的资助。他表示主要的挑战是在北冰洋如何平衡国家利益与全人类共同利益之间的关系。</p> <p>当然还有不同的论调。“今天，战略远距离洲际导弹或其他类似武器的威胁并不比冷战时期它们对人类的威胁小。实际上，在北冰洋冷战从未结束。”</p> <p>来自俄罗斯科学院亚历山大·维莱扎宁教授就是其中之一，他将在前任美国大使肯尼思·亚罗威茨，欧盟副主席戴安娜·华莱士及加拿大高级专员詹姆斯·莱特之后发言。</p> <p>会议上还有来自英国、丹麦、芬兰、并到及挪威等16个国家的高级代表发言。</p> <p>伯克曼表示，本次会议建立在跨越学术研究者、政府管理者、政治家及企业代表基础上，这将是朝着在北极地区建立推动合作阻止冲突战略迈进的第一步。</p> <p>正如斯塔夫里蒂斯所述：“融化的北极冰帽正在引起全世界的关注，因为它有可能改变这个一直被冷冻着的地区的地缘政治平衡。”</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/81758/141953?from=rss_related\">政府大臣下达禁肉强制令:少吃肉有益地球母亲健康</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/178539/141673?from=rss_related\">CNN民意测验：布什比奥巴马更好么？</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/164959/141935?from=rss_related\">《中国论》（第三回）——政治和文学的相关关系</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/140786?from=rss_related\">【外交政策】同时冉冉升起的“权二世”</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/66095/141918?from=rss_related\">【牛斯狗评论】匈牙利的红色警报（组图）</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804564/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804564/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804564/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472" (19636 2034) old 3 nil nil ((title nil "北约高官警告称气候变化可能导致北极冲突") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T07:02:10+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T07:02:10+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T07:02:10+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142472") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "迈克尔") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/181261")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/oct/11/nato-conflict-arctic-resources\">Climate change could lead to Arctic conflict, warns senior Nato commander | Environment | guardiancouk</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/181261\">迈克尔</a></p><h1>北约高官警告气候变化可能导致北极冲突</h1> <p id=\"stand-first\" class=\"stand-first-alone\">美国海军上将在即将召开的环境安全会谈前警告称，全球变暖和世界各国对资源的争夺可能在北极地区引发新一轮“冷战”。</p> <p class=\"third-party-tool reddit\" sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"53\">&nbsp;</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"63\">詹姆斯·G·斯塔夫里蒂斯将军是欧洲盟军最高指挥官，他的这番言论是针对即将在周三召开的北冰洋环境安全启动会议。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"63\">俄罗斯将参加本次会谈。会谈将以研讨会的形式进行，北约希望与莫斯科建立对话机制以避免第二次冷战发生。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"64\">“目前为止，北极地区的所有争议都通过和平手段解决。但是气候变化将使这个地区自然资源更容易获取，竞争将会加剧，目前的平衡也将被打破，”斯塔夫里蒂斯将军表示。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"64\">这位美国海军上将确信军事力量将在这个地区扮演重要角色 - 但主要是协助专家们开展工作，而这些专家却由商业或其他利益集团驱动。</p> <p>他还补充称：“全球领导人应该评估各国对北极地区兴趣的升温及气候变化带来的广泛影响，同时共同努力确保北极是一个合作的地区 - 而不是一个竞争或冲突的地方</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"65\">斯塔夫里蒂斯将军的观点是通过英国白厅的《北冰洋环境安全：推动合作组织冲突》报告的前言中阐述自己的观点，该报告的作者是剑桥大学北冰洋地缘政治学项目负责人保罗·伯克曼教授。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"67\">会议由于北极地区冰盖迅速融化而变得非常紧迫，因为这将导致开采石油和其他矿藏更加容易。会议将在伯克曼教授所在的斯科特极地研究所举办。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"68\">最近数周，Cairn Energy公司公布其在格林兰附近海域返现数个石油和天然气点，同时政府将授予多个开采证书。俄罗斯与挪威也在英国石油公司墨西哥湾漏油事故的阴影下在各自的北部地区采取相似的行动。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"71\">俄罗斯总理弗拉基米尔·普京两周前在莫斯科举行的北极国际论坛上的发言涉及到了所谓的“共同责任”。他也注意到，冰盖融化为石油和其他矿藏的运输提供了直接通道，但北极是一个“合作与对话的地区”。</p> <p>贝克曼教授作为本次研讨会的主要组织者，得到了北约和平与安全科学项目的资助。他表示主要的挑战是在北冰洋如何平衡国家利益与全人类共同利益之间的关系。</p> <p>当然还有不同的论调。“今天，战略远距离洲际导弹或其他类似武器的威胁并不比冷战时期它们对人类的威胁小。实际上，在北冰洋冷战从未结束。”</p> <p>来自俄罗斯科学院亚历山大·维莱扎宁教授就是其中之一，他将在前任美国大使肯尼思·亚罗威茨，欧盟副主席戴安娜·华莱士及加拿大高级专员詹姆斯·莱特之后发言。</p> <p>会议上还有来自英国、丹麦、芬兰、并到及挪威等16个国家的高级代表发言。</p> <p>伯克曼表示，本次会议建立在跨越学术研究者、政府管理者、政治家及企业代表基础上，这将是朝着在北极地区建立推动合作阻止冲突战略迈进的第一步。</p> <p>正如斯塔夫里蒂斯所述：“融化的北极冰帽正在引起全世界的关注，因为它有可能改变这个一直被冷冻着的地区的地缘政治平衡。”</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/81758/141953?from=rss_related\">政府大臣下达禁肉强制令:少吃肉有益地球母亲健康</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/178539/141673?from=rss_related\">CNN民意测验：布什比奥巴马更好么？</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/164959/141935?from=rss_related\">《中国论》（第三回）——政治和文学的相关关系</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/140786?from=rss_related\">【外交政策】同时冉冉升起的“权二世”</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/66095/141918?from=rss_related\">【牛斯狗评论】匈牙利的红色警报（组图）</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/oct/11/nato-conflict-arctic-resources\">Climate change could lead to Arctic conflict, warns senior Nato commander | Environment | guardiancouk</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/181261\">迈克尔</a></p><h1>北约高官警告气候变化可能导致北极冲突</h1> <p id=\"stand-first\" class=\"stand-first-alone\">美国海军上将在即将召开的环境安全会谈前警告称，全球变暖和世界各国对资源的争夺可能在北极地区引发新一轮“冷战”。</p> <p class=\"third-party-tool reddit\" sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"53\">&nbsp;</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"63\">詹姆斯·G·斯塔夫里蒂斯将军是欧洲盟军最高指挥官，他的这番言论是针对即将在周三召开的北冰洋环境安全启动会议。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"63\">俄罗斯将参加本次会谈。会谈将以研讨会的形式进行，北约希望与莫斯科建立对话机制以避免第二次冷战发生。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"64\">“目前为止，北极地区的所有争议都通过和平手段解决。但是气候变化将使这个地区自然资源更容易获取，竞争将会加剧，目前的平衡也将被打破，”斯塔夫里蒂斯将军表示。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"64\">这位美国海军上将确信军事力量将在这个地区扮演重要角色 - 但主要是协助专家们开展工作，而这些专家却由商业或其他利益集团驱动。</p> <p>他还补充称：“全球领导人应该评估各国对北极地区兴趣的升温及气候变化带来的广泛影响，同时共同努力确保北极是一个合作的地区 - 而不是一个竞争或冲突的地方</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"65\">斯塔夫里蒂斯将军的观点是通过英国白厅的《北冰洋环境安全：推动合作组织冲突》报告的前言中阐述自己的观点，该报告的作者是剑桥大学北冰洋地缘政治学项目负责人保罗·伯克曼教授。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"67\">会议由于北极地区冰盖迅速融化而变得非常紧迫，因为这将导致开采石油和其他矿藏更加容易。会议将在伯克曼教授所在的斯科特极地研究所举办。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"68\">最近数周，Cairn Energy公司公布其在格林兰附近海域返现数个石油和天然气点，同时政府将授予多个开采证书。俄罗斯与挪威也在英国石油公司墨西哥湾漏油事故的阴影下在各自的北部地区采取相似的行动。</p> <p sizcache=\"4\" sizset=\"71\">俄罗斯总理弗拉基米尔·普京两周前在莫斯科举行的北极国际论坛上的发言涉及到了所谓的“共同责任”。他也注意到，冰盖融化为石油和其他矿藏的运输提供了直接通道，但北极是一个“合作与对话的地区”。</p> <p>贝克曼教授作为本次研讨会的主要组织者，得到了北约和平与安全科学项目的资助。他表示主要的挑战是在北冰洋如何平衡国家利益与全人类共同利益之间的关系。</p> <p>当然还有不同的论调。“今天，战略远距离洲际导弹或其他类似武器的威胁并不比冷战时期它们对人类的威胁小。实际上，在北冰洋冷战从未结束。”</p> <p>来自俄罗斯科学院亚历山大·维莱扎宁教授就是其中之一，他将在前任美国大使肯尼思·亚罗威茨，欧盟副主席戴安娜·华莱士及加拿大高级专员詹姆斯·莱特之后发言。</p> <p>会议上还有来自英国、丹麦、芬兰、并到及挪威等16个国家的高级代表发言。</p> <p>伯克曼表示，本次会议建立在跨越学术研究者、政府管理者、政治家及企业代表基础上，这将是朝着在北极地区建立推动合作阻止冲突战略迈进的第一步。</p> <p>正如斯塔夫里蒂斯所述：“融化的北极冰帽正在引起全世界的关注，因为它有可能改变这个一直被冷冻着的地区的地缘政治平衡。”</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/81758/141953?from=rss_related\">政府大臣下达禁肉强制令:少吃肉有益地球母亲健康</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/178539/141673?from=rss_related\">CNN民意测验：布什比奥巴马更好么？</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/164959/141935?from=rss_related\">《中国论》（第三回）——政治和文学的相关关系</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/140786?from=rss_related\">【外交政策】同时冉冉升起的“权二世”</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/66095/141918?from=rss_related\">【牛斯狗评论】匈牙利的红色警报（组图）</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804564/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804564/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804564/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>") (pubDate nil "Tue, 12 Oct 2010 15:02:10 +0800") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142472") (dc:creator nil "迈克尔") (fs:srclink nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/181261/142472") (fs:srcfeed nil "http://www.yeeyan.org/feed/category/310") (fs:itemid nil "feedsky/yeeyan-science/~8024232/422804564/5034837"))) ("别有洞天的水晶宫，出离美丽" "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/10/101007-lost-crystal-caves-mexico-science-mine-superman-ice-palace/\">Giant Crystal Caves Yield New &quot;Ice Palace,&quot; More</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/174944\">Billie W</a></p><blockquote>Giant Crystal Caves Yield New \"Ice Palace,\" More </blockquote> <p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;别有洞天的水晶宫，出离美丽</span></strong></p> <blockquote>In hellish conditions, explorers find biological mysteries, \"alien\" environments.</blockquote> <p>在地狱般的条件下，探险家们发现了神秘奇异的生命环境。</p> <blockquote>Ker Than</blockquote> <p>Ker Than</p> <blockquote>for National Geographic News</blockquote> <p>国家地理新闻</p> <blockquote>Published October 7, 2010</blockquote> <p>2010年10月7日发表</p> <blockquote>It looks like Superman's Fortress of Solitude and is nearly as hard to get into, but that hasn't stopped explorers from uncovering new secrets in and around Mexico's deep, deadly hot Cave of Crystals. </blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这里就像是超人归来中的孤独要塞（电影名——译者注），极难进入，但这些困难都无法阻挡探险家们揭示自然奥秘的步伐——他们进入了墨西哥深邃且酷热的晶体岩洞。</p> <blockquote>Outfitted with ice-cooled suits, teams have found biological mysteries, parallels with other planets, and the \"Ice Palace,\" an unexplored cavern lined with rare crystal formations—and just in time too. Parts of the complex may soon be returned to their natural, submerged states.</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在隔热服的全副武装保护下，探险队发现了与其它星球相比更为神秘的生命踪迹，更出人意料的是，“水晶宫”——一个布满罕见晶体结构的大洞穴——也同时被发现。</p> <blockquote>A thousand feet (304 meter) underground, the Cave of Crystals (pictures) is just one of a series of glittering caverns beneath the Chihuahuan Desert's Naica mountain (map). Much of the complex would naturally be filled with scorching water, were it not for industrial pumps that facilitate the mining of silver, zinc, lead, and other minerals in the caves.</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 约一千英尺（304米）的地下，晶体岩洞（如图所示）仅仅是奇瓦瓦沙漠中的奈卡山脉下一系列绚烂夺目的洞穴之一。<span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">洞穴中大多充满灼热的水，因而给利用工业泵在其中进行银、锌、铅等矿物的开采增加了难度。</span></p> <blockquote>In the two-story-tall, football-field-size Cave of Crystals, enormous beams of gypsum—among the largest freestanding crystals in the world—sprout haphazardly from the ceiling, floor, and walls. Individually, though, the crystals appear anything but haphazard, sporting the sharp, geometric appearance that scientists call euhedral.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">层楼高，足球场大小的晶体岩洞中，巨大的石膏岩（也称玄精石——译者注）晶体柱——世界上最大的独立晶体——杂乱无章地由岩洞的顶部、地面和岩壁出生发出来。尽管相互独立，这些晶体的外观并非毫无规律，它们突变出尖锐的具有几何形的外表，科学家称之为自形。</span></p> <blockquote>This jewel-like effect makes the giant crystals truly unique, according to John Rakovan, a mineralogist at Miami University in Ohio, who was not involved in the project.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; John Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">指出，珠宝样的外观赋予了这些巨大的晶体以绝对的独特性。他是俄亥俄州迈阿密大学的矿物学家，并没有加入这个研究项目。</span></p> <blockquote>\"When crystals get larger and larger, they become less euhedral, typically\"—and more rocklike. \"Scientists didn't think it was possible to get large crystals that are so morphologically perfect\" before the Cave of Crystals discovery, Rakovan said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;“随着晶体越长越大，它们的自形性会逐渐减弱，一般都是这样”——更像是岩石。在发现这个晶体岩洞之前“科学家们认为巨大的晶体不可能具有如此完美的形态”在，</span><span>Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>The translucent columns also resemble giant pillars of ice but are warmed by superheated air leaking up from underground magma chambers.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这些剔透的柱体就像巨大的冰柱，但又被过热的空气熔化，这些空气来自地下的岩浆房。</span></p> <blockquote>The combination of 90 percent humidity and a temperature of 118 degrees Fahrenheit (48 degrees Celsius) inside the cave can kill an unprepared human in just 30 minutes.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在洞穴的内部，在</span><span>90%</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">湿度和华氏</span><span>118</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">度（</span><span>4</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;\">8</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;\">℃</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">）高温的共同作用下，毫无防备的人进入，将在</span><span>30</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分钟内死亡。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's a terrible and magical environment all at the same time,\" said Penelope Boston, an astrobiologist and cave scientist who appears in the new documentary Into the Lost Crystal Caves, which airs Sunday at 8 p.m. ET/PT on the National Geographic Channel. (The National Geographic Channel is part-owned by the National Geographic Society, which owns National Geographic News.)</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “这是一个恐怖的环境，但同时它又是神奇的，”</span><span>Penelope Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他是一位宇宙生物学家和洞穴科学家。此人在新节目“走进迷失的晶体洞穴”中露过面，这个节目在国家地理频道每周日晚</span><span>8</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">点</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">播送。（国家地理学会拥有国家地理频道的一部分，它同时还负责国家地理新闻。）</span></p> <blockquote>Beyond the Cave of Crystals</blockquote> <p><strong>晶体洞穴之上</strong></p> <blockquote>Discovered by miners in 2000, the Cave of Crystals is just one chamber in what appears to be a network of subterranean caverns beneath Naica—some well known and evocatively named: the Cave of Swords, the Queen's Eye, the Cave of Sails.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2000</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年被矿工发现时，晶体洞穴还仅仅是奈卡山脉地下洞穴系统的其中之一——其中的一些十分著名且有上口的名字：剑之洞，女王之眼，以及蜗牛洞。</span></p> <blockquote>In 2009 a video camera attached to a drill bit found hints of one more crystal-lined cave during the creation of the Robin Hole, a 2,000-foot-deep (600-meter-deep) ventilation shaft meant to cool mining tunnels below.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>,</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">安装在钻头上的摄像机捕捉到了又一个遍布晶体的洞穴的存迹，它正处于罗宾洞的形成时期，这是一个</span><span>2,000</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">英尺深的通风井，对冷却下面的矿道起着重要的作用。</span></p> <blockquote>Descending into the hole months later, in December 2009, a scientific team confirmed the new, naturally dry crystal cave about 500 feet (150 meters) below the surface.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 数月之后的</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>12</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">月，一个科考队深入了这个洞穴，他们确认这是一个新的自然风干形成的晶体洞穴，位于大约</span><span>500</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">英尺</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">（</span><span>150</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">米</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">）的地下。</span></p> <blockquote>Dubbed the Ice Palace, the new cave lacks giant pillars, but sparkles with rare crystal formations, including minerals resembling cauliflower and fiber-optic-like filaments.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管被称为水晶宫，这个新发现的洞穴缺少巨大的支柱，但是有趣的是它具有罕见的晶体构成，包括类似花椰菜的矿物和光线样的丝状物。</span></p> <blockquote>The mysteries of the Ice Palace will likely remain unsolved, however. The Industrias Peñoles mining company has decided to cover the Robin Hole and has also hinted that it may shut down the expensive water pumps that keep the Cave of Crystals dry, according to the documentary.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 然而，水晶宫的奥秘仍待解决。</span><span>Industrias Peñoles</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">矿业公司已经决定封存罗宾洞，并且暗示，可能关停昂贵的水泵。根据文件资料，该水泵原来是用于保持水晶洞干燥的。</span></p> <blockquote>\"I don't think they'll ever be able to preserve those caves,\" Miami University's Rakovan said. \"It'll be economically unfeasible.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我认为他们没有能力保存那些洞穴，”迈阿密大学的</span><span>Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“这在经济上是不可行的。”</span></p> <blockquote>But shutting down the caves isn't necessarily a bad thing, Rakovan added. \"It might actually preserve the crystals. And if at a later date it becomes important to get in there again, they could repump.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 但是关停洞穴并不是十分必要的坏事，</span><span>Rakobvan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">补充道。“实际上，它可能保存住晶体。而且一旦日后需要再次进入洞穴，他们就得重新起泵。”</span></p> <blockquote>Ice-Cooled Suits Required</blockquote> <p><strong>进入洞穴需要制冷服</strong></p> <blockquote>Exploring the Naica caves requires more than just industrial strength water pumps. Scientists entering the complex in 2008 and 2009 wore custom-made, 45-pound (25-kilograms) cooling suits that extend mission times from 15 minutes to an hour.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 进入奈卡洞穴探险需要除工业用水泵外更多的防护。在</span><span>2008</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">和</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年间，科学家们进入这些复杂的洞穴系统是穿着制冷服的，这种服装是当地生产的，重达</span><span>45</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">磅</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">（</span><span>25</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">公斤</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">），能够将任务时间由</span><span>15</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分钟延长至</span><span>1</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时。</span></p> <blockquote>Each suit contains several ice-filled compartments as well as respirators connected to ice-filled backpacks, which send cool air to the wearer's lungs. Masks protect the eyes, which can scorch in the cave's heat.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 制冷服包含着若干由冰充满的部件，以及连在冰背囊上的人工呼吸机，它可以将冷却的空气传送至使用者的肺部。面罩则用来保护眼睛，眼睛在洞穴的高温下会被烤焦。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's funny, because when you look at the pictures of us in there in the suits, it looks like we're in an ice chamber, but it's just the reverse,\" said Boston, of the New Mexico Institute of Mining and Technology.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “这真有趣，因为当你看到我们穿着冷却服在洞里的照片，觉得好像我们是在一个冰冻的环境，但事实恰恰相反，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他来自矿物与科技的新墨西哥研究所。</span></p> <blockquote>Even with the protective gear, the scientists often operated at the edge of safety.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 即使有保护装置，科学家们仍然常常是在危险的边缘进行工作。</span></p> <blockquote>Ontario, Canada-based astrophysicist Sara Poirier said, \"We all just kept pushing further and further [into the cave], so by the time you are heading back, you've pushed yourself beyond the limits that are safe\"—and that's with the gear operating properly.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 安大略，加拿大背景的天体物理学家</span><span>Sara Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，“我们都坚持不断向洞穴深处推进，所以当你回望时，你已经将自己推向了安全限度之外”——所谓安全限度就是正确地使用防护装置。</span></p> <blockquote>At least one piece of equipment offered little protection. The portable Ice Cube—a newly designed, air-cooled, transparent tent designed to allow for two-hour Naica-caves missions—never cooled down enough to bring overheated bodies back to safe levels.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 至少有一套设备能提供点儿防护。便携式冰箱——一种新研发的，可用于空气冷却的透明帐篷，可令科学家们在奈卡洞穴中工作</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时——奈卡洞穴自身不能冷却到足够低的温度来使过热的肌体恢复至安全的水平。</span></p> <blockquote>Microbial Mystery in Cave of Crystals</blockquote> <p><strong>晶体洞穴中的微生物奇迹</strong></p> <blockquote>Though the calling card of the horseshoe-shaped Cave of Crystals may be its massive mineral formations, some of its biggest surprises are literally microscopic.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管马蹄形水晶洞穴的标志物就是它宏伟的矿物结构，然而它最令人惊叹的地方却是显微水平的。</span></p> <blockquote>In 2008 a team of scientists, including New Mexico Tech's Boston, investigated the cave and found microbial life living in tiny air pockets in the crystals.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2008</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年，一个科考队的专家，包括新墨西哥研究所的</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">，调查了这个洞穴并在一个晶体中的气穴中发现存活着微生物。</span></p> <blockquote>In December 2009 Boston returned to the cave with another team. From pools of water that hadn't been present during her first trip, the scientists collected bacteria as well as viruses that prey on the bacteria—something that was suspected but had not been confirmed on the first expedition.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>12</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">月</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">与另一组科考队重返洞穴。在一湾第一次未曾发现的水中科学家们发现了细菌以及寄生于细菌的病毒——在第一次探险中怀疑存在这些生物，但当时并未确认。</span></p> <blockquote>Viruses, after all, are among the \"primary predators of bacteria,\" explained Danielle Winget, a biologist at the University of British Columbia, in the new documentary.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 病毒，归根结底，属于“细菌的初级捕食者，”</span><span>Danielle Winget</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">在一份新文献中解释道，他是英属哥伦比亚大学的生物学家。</span></p> <blockquote>Sure enough, the team found as many as 200 million viruses in a single drop of Cave of Crystals water.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 的确，科考队发现，在晶体岩洞的一滴水中包含着</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">亿个病毒。</span></p> <blockquote>But the virus finding was perhaps not the expedition's most surprising microbial discovery. Analysis of bacterial DNA from the Cave of Crystals showed that the tiny life-forms are related to microbes living in other extreme environments around the world, including caves in South Africa and Australia as well as hydrothermal vents (video).</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 但是，也许病毒的发现并不是此次探险中最令人惊讶的微生物发现。对晶体岩洞中的细菌的</span><span>DNA</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分析显示这些微小的生命形式与在世界上的另外一些极端微生物相关，它们生存环境包括南非的岩洞和澳大利亚的热泉口。</span></p> <blockquote>\"We're picking up these patterns of similarities in places that are geographically widely separated,\" Boston said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我们在地理上广泛分布的很多地点都提取到了这些相似的模式，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>That similarity and separation adds up to a mystery, according to Curtis Suttle, a biologist at University of British Columbia and a member of the 2009 Cave of Crystals expedition.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这些相似性与分离性共同造就了如此的神秘，</span><span>Curtis Suttle</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他是英属哥伦比亚大学的生物学家，同时也是</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年水晶洞穴科考队的成员之一。</span></p> <blockquote>\"We don't really understand how it is that the organisms in a hydrothermal vent in Greece or a deep gold mine in South Africa are related to organisms that we find in a subsurface cave\" at Naica, Suttle said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我们并不真正的明白在希腊热泉口或者南非深邃金矿处的生物是如何与我们在奈卡发现的地下洞穴的生物产生关联的”</span><span>Suttle</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's hard to imagine some kind of underground [network] connecting South Africa with Mexico.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “很难想象在南非和墨西哥之间存在着地下网络的联系。”</span></p> <blockquote>Alien Underworlds</blockquote> <p><strong>外来的地下世界</strong></p> <blockquote>As mind-boggling as the idea of a possibly globe-spanning, underground bacterial network may be, some scientists see potential links between the Cave of Crystals and even farther-flung hot spots—for example, extreme environments on Mars and other worlds.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 有这样一个令人难以置信的观点，认为可能存在着全球范围的地下细菌网络，一些科学家看到了晶体洞穴和更加热门的领域的潜在联系——例如，在火星和其他星球上的极端环境。</span></p> <blockquote>Though Martian geology might be more static overall than Earth's, \"there may be residual pockets of geothermal activity that could provide a zone where water could be liquid and where chemically reduced gases from below can percolate up and act as a nutrient source,\" as in the Cave of Crystals, Boston said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管火星的地质状况整体上比地球稳定，“仍可能存在地热活动的残留穴，可能提供一个使水保持液态的区域，使得地下的化学还原性气体能够渗出并起到晶体洞穴中氮源的作用，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>Poirier, the Ontario astrophysicist, agreed.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">，安大略的天体物理学家，也同意这个观点。</span></p> <blockquote>\"For Mars, our best bet of finding life is to look underground,\" Poirier said. \"So there are a lot of parallels between humans exploring subterranean caves looking for microbes and Martian exploration in the future.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “对于火星，我们最有把握找到生命的地方是地下，”</span><span>Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“人们做了大量相似的工作去探索地下洞穴以及将来对火星的探索，以期发现微生物。”</span></p> <blockquote>If the caves on Mars are anything like the caverns beneath Naica mountain, she said, future Martian explorers will have to be trained to ignore the strange sights surrounding them.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 如果火星上的洞穴与奈卡山脉下的洞穴有些许相似，她说，未来的火星探险者就得学着无视他们周围奇妙的景观。</span></p> <blockquote>\"When you're in the caves, you're overwhelmed by the [harsh] conditions, but you're also overwhelmed by the beauty, and it's really hard to maintain your focus,\" she said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “当你身处洞穴，恶劣的环境条件会令你不知所措，但同时你又会被它的美丽深深折服，这使得你很难集中注意力，”她说。</span></p> <blockquote>Even if scalding water submerges that beauty tomorrow, Boston said, the caves' scientific potential should live on, thanks to the multitude of samples already collected.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 即使有朝一日沸水淹没了这美丽的景观，</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，洞穴的学术潜力也将持续存在下去，因为我们已经收集了大量的样品。</span></p> <blockquote>\"My usual rule of thumb is for every hour you spend in the field, you spend at least a thousand hours on analysis,\" Boston said. \"So we've got our hands full.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我的经验是，如果你采样花了</span><span>1</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时，那么你将花费上千倍的时间来分析它，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“所以我们的任务很重。”</span></p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190?from=rss_related\">重返水晶宫</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/141464?from=rss_related\">珊瑚美景</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/lost/141674?from=rss_related\">卫报图说－－本周野生动物图集</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/38018/137545?from=rss_related\">机场之最：奇异、古怪、可怕</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/173183/134103?from=rss_related\">【图集】18座最奇特的人工岛</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804571/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804571/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804571/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283" (19635 62727) old 4 nil nil ((title nil "别有洞天的水晶宫，出离美丽") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T05:41:27+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T05:41:27+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T05:41:27+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142283") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "Billie W") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/174944")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/10/101007-lost-crystal-caves-mexico-science-mine-superman-ice-palace/\">Giant Crystal Caves Yield New &quot;Ice Palace,&quot; More</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/174944\">Billie W</a></p><blockquote>Giant Crystal Caves Yield New \"Ice Palace,\" More </blockquote> <p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;别有洞天的水晶宫，出离美丽</span></strong></p> <blockquote>In hellish conditions, explorers find biological mysteries, \"alien\" environments.</blockquote> <p>在地狱般的条件下，探险家们发现了神秘奇异的生命环境。</p> <blockquote>Ker Than</blockquote> <p>Ker Than</p> <blockquote>for National Geographic News</blockquote> <p>国家地理新闻</p> <blockquote>Published October 7, 2010</blockquote> <p>2010年10月7日发表</p> <blockquote>It looks like Superman's Fortress of Solitude and is nearly as hard to get into, but that hasn't stopped explorers from uncovering new secrets in and around Mexico's deep, deadly hot Cave of Crystals. </blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这里就像是超人归来中的孤独要塞（电影名——译者注），极难进入，但这些困难都无法阻挡探险家们揭示自然奥秘的步伐——他们进入了墨西哥深邃且酷热的晶体岩洞。</p> <blockquote>Outfitted with ice-cooled suits, teams have found biological mysteries, parallels with other planets, and the \"Ice Palace,\" an unexplored cavern lined with rare crystal formations—and just in time too. Parts of the complex may soon be returned to their natural, submerged states.</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在隔热服的全副武装保护下，探险队发现了与其它星球相比更为神秘的生命踪迹，更出人意料的是，“水晶宫”——一个布满罕见晶体结构的大洞穴——也同时被发现。</p> <blockquote>A thousand feet (304 meter) underground, the Cave of Crystals (pictures) is just one of a series of glittering caverns beneath the Chihuahuan Desert's Naica mountain (map). Much of the complex would naturally be filled with scorching water, were it not for industrial pumps that facilitate the mining of silver, zinc, lead, and other minerals in the caves.</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 约一千英尺（304米）的地下，晶体岩洞（如图所示）仅仅是奇瓦瓦沙漠中的奈卡山脉下一系列绚烂夺目的洞穴之一。<span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">洞穴中大多充满灼热的水，因而给利用工业泵在其中进行银、锌、铅等矿物的开采增加了难度。</span></p> <blockquote>In the two-story-tall, football-field-size Cave of Crystals, enormous beams of gypsum—among the largest freestanding crystals in the world—sprout haphazardly from the ceiling, floor, and walls. Individually, though, the crystals appear anything but haphazard, sporting the sharp, geometric appearance that scientists call euhedral.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">层楼高，足球场大小的晶体岩洞中，巨大的石膏岩（也称玄精石——译者注）晶体柱——世界上最大的独立晶体——杂乱无章地由岩洞的顶部、地面和岩壁出生发出来。尽管相互独立，这些晶体的外观并非毫无规律，它们突变出尖锐的具有几何形的外表，科学家称之为自形。</span></p> <blockquote>This jewel-like effect makes the giant crystals truly unique, according to John Rakovan, a mineralogist at Miami University in Ohio, who was not involved in the project.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; John Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">指出，珠宝样的外观赋予了这些巨大的晶体以绝对的独特性。他是俄亥俄州迈阿密大学的矿物学家，并没有加入这个研究项目。</span></p> <blockquote>\"When crystals get larger and larger, they become less euhedral, typically\"—and more rocklike. \"Scientists didn't think it was possible to get large crystals that are so morphologically perfect\" before the Cave of Crystals discovery, Rakovan said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;“随着晶体越长越大，它们的自形性会逐渐减弱，一般都是这样”——更像是岩石。在发现这个晶体岩洞之前“科学家们认为巨大的晶体不可能具有如此完美的形态”在，</span><span>Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>The translucent columns also resemble giant pillars of ice but are warmed by superheated air leaking up from underground magma chambers.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这些剔透的柱体就像巨大的冰柱，但又被过热的空气熔化，这些空气来自地下的岩浆房。</span></p> <blockquote>The combination of 90 percent humidity and a temperature of 118 degrees Fahrenheit (48 degrees Celsius) inside the cave can kill an unprepared human in just 30 minutes.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在洞穴的内部，在</span><span>90%</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">湿度和华氏</span><span>118</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">度（</span><span>4</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;\">8</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;\">℃</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">）高温的共同作用下，毫无防备的人进入，将在</span><span>30</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分钟内死亡。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's a terrible and magical environment all at the same time,\" said Penelope Boston, an astrobiologist and cave scientist who appears in the new documentary Into the Lost Crystal Caves, which airs Sunday at 8 p.m. ET/PT on the National Geographic Channel. (The National Geographic Channel is part-owned by the National Geographic Society, which owns National Geographic News.)</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “这是一个恐怖的环境，但同时它又是神奇的，”</span><span>Penelope Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他是一位宇宙生物学家和洞穴科学家。此人在新节目“走进迷失的晶体洞穴”中露过面，这个节目在国家地理频道每周日晚</span><span>8</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">点</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">播送。（国家地理学会拥有国家地理频道的一部分，它同时还负责国家地理新闻。）</span></p> <blockquote>Beyond the Cave of Crystals</blockquote> <p><strong>晶体洞穴之上</strong></p> <blockquote>Discovered by miners in 2000, the Cave of Crystals is just one chamber in what appears to be a network of subterranean caverns beneath Naica—some well known and evocatively named: the Cave of Swords, the Queen's Eye, the Cave of Sails.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2000</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年被矿工发现时，晶体洞穴还仅仅是奈卡山脉地下洞穴系统的其中之一——其中的一些十分著名且有上口的名字：剑之洞，女王之眼，以及蜗牛洞。</span></p> <blockquote>In 2009 a video camera attached to a drill bit found hints of one more crystal-lined cave during the creation of the Robin Hole, a 2,000-foot-deep (600-meter-deep) ventilation shaft meant to cool mining tunnels below.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>,</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">安装在钻头上的摄像机捕捉到了又一个遍布晶体的洞穴的存迹，它正处于罗宾洞的形成时期，这是一个</span><span>2,000</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">英尺深的通风井，对冷却下面的矿道起着重要的作用。</span></p> <blockquote>Descending into the hole months later, in December 2009, a scientific team confirmed the new, naturally dry crystal cave about 500 feet (150 meters) below the surface.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 数月之后的</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>12</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">月，一个科考队深入了这个洞穴，他们确认这是一个新的自然风干形成的晶体洞穴，位于大约</span><span>500</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">英尺</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">（</span><span>150</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">米</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">）的地下。</span></p> <blockquote>Dubbed the Ice Palace, the new cave lacks giant pillars, but sparkles with rare crystal formations, including minerals resembling cauliflower and fiber-optic-like filaments.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管被称为水晶宫，这个新发现的洞穴缺少巨大的支柱，但是有趣的是它具有罕见的晶体构成，包括类似花椰菜的矿物和光线样的丝状物。</span></p> <blockquote>The mysteries of the Ice Palace will likely remain unsolved, however. The Industrias Peñoles mining company has decided to cover the Robin Hole and has also hinted that it may shut down the expensive water pumps that keep the Cave of Crystals dry, according to the documentary.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 然而，水晶宫的奥秘仍待解决。</span><span>Industrias Peñoles</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">矿业公司已经决定封存罗宾洞，并且暗示，可能关停昂贵的水泵。根据文件资料，该水泵原来是用于保持水晶洞干燥的。</span></p> <blockquote>\"I don't think they'll ever be able to preserve those caves,\" Miami University's Rakovan said. \"It'll be economically unfeasible.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我认为他们没有能力保存那些洞穴，”迈阿密大学的</span><span>Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“这在经济上是不可行的。”</span></p> <blockquote>But shutting down the caves isn't necessarily a bad thing, Rakovan added. \"It might actually preserve the crystals. And if at a later date it becomes important to get in there again, they could repump.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 但是关停洞穴并不是十分必要的坏事，</span><span>Rakobvan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">补充道。“实际上，它可能保存住晶体。而且一旦日后需要再次进入洞穴，他们就得重新起泵。”</span></p> <blockquote>Ice-Cooled Suits Required</blockquote> <p><strong>进入洞穴需要制冷服</strong></p> <blockquote>Exploring the Naica caves requires more than just industrial strength water pumps. Scientists entering the complex in 2008 and 2009 wore custom-made, 45-pound (25-kilograms) cooling suits that extend mission times from 15 minutes to an hour.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 进入奈卡洞穴探险需要除工业用水泵外更多的防护。在</span><span>2008</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">和</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年间，科学家们进入这些复杂的洞穴系统是穿着制冷服的，这种服装是当地生产的，重达</span><span>45</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">磅</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">（</span><span>25</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">公斤</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">），能够将任务时间由</span><span>15</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分钟延长至</span><span>1</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时。</span></p> <blockquote>Each suit contains several ice-filled compartments as well as respirators connected to ice-filled backpacks, which send cool air to the wearer's lungs. Masks protect the eyes, which can scorch in the cave's heat.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 制冷服包含着若干由冰充满的部件，以及连在冰背囊上的人工呼吸机，它可以将冷却的空气传送至使用者的肺部。面罩则用来保护眼睛，眼睛在洞穴的高温下会被烤焦。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's funny, because when you look at the pictures of us in there in the suits, it looks like we're in an ice chamber, but it's just the reverse,\" said Boston, of the New Mexico Institute of Mining and Technology.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “这真有趣，因为当你看到我们穿着冷却服在洞里的照片，觉得好像我们是在一个冰冻的环境，但事实恰恰相反，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他来自矿物与科技的新墨西哥研究所。</span></p> <blockquote>Even with the protective gear, the scientists often operated at the edge of safety.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 即使有保护装置，科学家们仍然常常是在危险的边缘进行工作。</span></p> <blockquote>Ontario, Canada-based astrophysicist Sara Poirier said, \"We all just kept pushing further and further [into the cave], so by the time you are heading back, you've pushed yourself beyond the limits that are safe\"—and that's with the gear operating properly.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 安大略，加拿大背景的天体物理学家</span><span>Sara Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，“我们都坚持不断向洞穴深处推进，所以当你回望时，你已经将自己推向了安全限度之外”——所谓安全限度就是正确地使用防护装置。</span></p> <blockquote>At least one piece of equipment offered little protection. The portable Ice Cube—a newly designed, air-cooled, transparent tent designed to allow for two-hour Naica-caves missions—never cooled down enough to bring overheated bodies back to safe levels.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 至少有一套设备能提供点儿防护。便携式冰箱——一种新研发的，可用于空气冷却的透明帐篷，可令科学家们在奈卡洞穴中工作</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时——奈卡洞穴自身不能冷却到足够低的温度来使过热的肌体恢复至安全的水平。</span></p> <blockquote>Microbial Mystery in Cave of Crystals</blockquote> <p><strong>晶体洞穴中的微生物奇迹</strong></p> <blockquote>Though the calling card of the horseshoe-shaped Cave of Crystals may be its massive mineral formations, some of its biggest surprises are literally microscopic.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管马蹄形水晶洞穴的标志物就是它宏伟的矿物结构，然而它最令人惊叹的地方却是显微水平的。</span></p> <blockquote>In 2008 a team of scientists, including New Mexico Tech's Boston, investigated the cave and found microbial life living in tiny air pockets in the crystals.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2008</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年，一个科考队的专家，包括新墨西哥研究所的</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">，调查了这个洞穴并在一个晶体中的气穴中发现存活着微生物。</span></p> <blockquote>In December 2009 Boston returned to the cave with another team. From pools of water that hadn't been present during her first trip, the scientists collected bacteria as well as viruses that prey on the bacteria—something that was suspected but had not been confirmed on the first expedition.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>12</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">月</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">与另一组科考队重返洞穴。在一湾第一次未曾发现的水中科学家们发现了细菌以及寄生于细菌的病毒——在第一次探险中怀疑存在这些生物，但当时并未确认。</span></p> <blockquote>Viruses, after all, are among the \"primary predators of bacteria,\" explained Danielle Winget, a biologist at the University of British Columbia, in the new documentary.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 病毒，归根结底，属于“细菌的初级捕食者，”</span><span>Danielle Winget</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">在一份新文献中解释道，他是英属哥伦比亚大学的生物学家。</span></p> <blockquote>Sure enough, the team found as many as 200 million viruses in a single drop of Cave of Crystals water.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 的确，科考队发现，在晶体岩洞的一滴水中包含着</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">亿个病毒。</span></p> <blockquote>But the virus finding was perhaps not the expedition's most surprising microbial discovery. Analysis of bacterial DNA from the Cave of Crystals showed that the tiny life-forms are related to microbes living in other extreme environments around the world, including caves in South Africa and Australia as well as hydrothermal vents (video).</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 但是，也许病毒的发现并不是此次探险中最令人惊讶的微生物发现。对晶体岩洞中的细菌的</span><span>DNA</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分析显示这些微小的生命形式与在世界上的另外一些极端微生物相关，它们生存环境包括南非的岩洞和澳大利亚的热泉口。</span></p> <blockquote>\"We're picking up these patterns of similarities in places that are geographically widely separated,\" Boston said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我们在地理上广泛分布的很多地点都提取到了这些相似的模式，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>That similarity and separation adds up to a mystery, according to Curtis Suttle, a biologist at University of British Columbia and a member of the 2009 Cave of Crystals expedition.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这些相似性与分离性共同造就了如此的神秘，</span><span>Curtis Suttle</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他是英属哥伦比亚大学的生物学家，同时也是</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年水晶洞穴科考队的成员之一。</span></p> <blockquote>\"We don't really understand how it is that the organisms in a hydrothermal vent in Greece or a deep gold mine in South Africa are related to organisms that we find in a subsurface cave\" at Naica, Suttle said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我们并不真正的明白在希腊热泉口或者南非深邃金矿处的生物是如何与我们在奈卡发现的地下洞穴的生物产生关联的”</span><span>Suttle</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's hard to imagine some kind of underground [network] connecting South Africa with Mexico.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “很难想象在南非和墨西哥之间存在着地下网络的联系。”</span></p> <blockquote>Alien Underworlds</blockquote> <p><strong>外来的地下世界</strong></p> <blockquote>As mind-boggling as the idea of a possibly globe-spanning, underground bacterial network may be, some scientists see potential links between the Cave of Crystals and even farther-flung hot spots—for example, extreme environments on Mars and other worlds.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 有这样一个令人难以置信的观点，认为可能存在着全球范围的地下细菌网络，一些科学家看到了晶体洞穴和更加热门的领域的潜在联系——例如，在火星和其他星球上的极端环境。</span></p> <blockquote>Though Martian geology might be more static overall than Earth's, \"there may be residual pockets of geothermal activity that could provide a zone where water could be liquid and where chemically reduced gases from below can percolate up and act as a nutrient source,\" as in the Cave of Crystals, Boston said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管火星的地质状况整体上比地球稳定，“仍可能存在地热活动的残留穴，可能提供一个使水保持液态的区域，使得地下的化学还原性气体能够渗出并起到晶体洞穴中氮源的作用，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>Poirier, the Ontario astrophysicist, agreed.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">，安大略的天体物理学家，也同意这个观点。</span></p> <blockquote>\"For Mars, our best bet of finding life is to look underground,\" Poirier said. \"So there are a lot of parallels between humans exploring subterranean caves looking for microbes and Martian exploration in the future.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “对于火星，我们最有把握找到生命的地方是地下，”</span><span>Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“人们做了大量相似的工作去探索地下洞穴以及将来对火星的探索，以期发现微生物。”</span></p> <blockquote>If the caves on Mars are anything like the caverns beneath Naica mountain, she said, future Martian explorers will have to be trained to ignore the strange sights surrounding them.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 如果火星上的洞穴与奈卡山脉下的洞穴有些许相似，她说，未来的火星探险者就得学着无视他们周围奇妙的景观。</span></p> <blockquote>\"When you're in the caves, you're overwhelmed by the [harsh] conditions, but you're also overwhelmed by the beauty, and it's really hard to maintain your focus,\" she said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “当你身处洞穴，恶劣的环境条件会令你不知所措，但同时你又会被它的美丽深深折服，这使得你很难集中注意力，”她说。</span></p> <blockquote>Even if scalding water submerges that beauty tomorrow, Boston said, the caves' scientific potential should live on, thanks to the multitude of samples already collected.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 即使有朝一日沸水淹没了这美丽的景观，</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，洞穴的学术潜力也将持续存在下去，因为我们已经收集了大量的样品。</span></p> <blockquote>\"My usual rule of thumb is for every hour you spend in the field, you spend at least a thousand hours on analysis,\" Boston said. \"So we've got our hands full.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我的经验是，如果你采样花了</span><span>1</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时，那么你将花费上千倍的时间来分析它，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“所以我们的任务很重。”</span></p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190?from=rss_related\">重返水晶宫</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/141464?from=rss_related\">珊瑚美景</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/lost/141674?from=rss_related\">卫报图说－－本周野生动物图集</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/38018/137545?from=rss_related\">机场之最：奇异、古怪、可怕</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/173183/134103?from=rss_related\">【图集】18座最奇特的人工岛</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/10/101007-lost-crystal-caves-mexico-science-mine-superman-ice-palace/\">Giant Crystal Caves Yield New &quot;Ice Palace,&quot; More</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/174944\">Billie W</a></p><blockquote>Giant Crystal Caves Yield New \"Ice Palace,\" More </blockquote> <p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;别有洞天的水晶宫，出离美丽</span></strong></p> <blockquote>In hellish conditions, explorers find biological mysteries, \"alien\" environments.</blockquote> <p>在地狱般的条件下，探险家们发现了神秘奇异的生命环境。</p> <blockquote>Ker Than</blockquote> <p>Ker Than</p> <blockquote>for National Geographic News</blockquote> <p>国家地理新闻</p> <blockquote>Published October 7, 2010</blockquote> <p>2010年10月7日发表</p> <blockquote>It looks like Superman's Fortress of Solitude and is nearly as hard to get into, but that hasn't stopped explorers from uncovering new secrets in and around Mexico's deep, deadly hot Cave of Crystals. </blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这里就像是超人归来中的孤独要塞（电影名——译者注），极难进入，但这些困难都无法阻挡探险家们揭示自然奥秘的步伐——他们进入了墨西哥深邃且酷热的晶体岩洞。</p> <blockquote>Outfitted with ice-cooled suits, teams have found biological mysteries, parallels with other planets, and the \"Ice Palace,\" an unexplored cavern lined with rare crystal formations—and just in time too. Parts of the complex may soon be returned to their natural, submerged states.</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在隔热服的全副武装保护下，探险队发现了与其它星球相比更为神秘的生命踪迹，更出人意料的是，“水晶宫”——一个布满罕见晶体结构的大洞穴——也同时被发现。</p> <blockquote>A thousand feet (304 meter) underground, the Cave of Crystals (pictures) is just one of a series of glittering caverns beneath the Chihuahuan Desert's Naica mountain (map). Much of the complex would naturally be filled with scorching water, were it not for industrial pumps that facilitate the mining of silver, zinc, lead, and other minerals in the caves.</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 约一千英尺（304米）的地下，晶体岩洞（如图所示）仅仅是奇瓦瓦沙漠中的奈卡山脉下一系列绚烂夺目的洞穴之一。<span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">洞穴中大多充满灼热的水，因而给利用工业泵在其中进行银、锌、铅等矿物的开采增加了难度。</span></p> <blockquote>In the two-story-tall, football-field-size Cave of Crystals, enormous beams of gypsum—among the largest freestanding crystals in the world—sprout haphazardly from the ceiling, floor, and walls. Individually, though, the crystals appear anything but haphazard, sporting the sharp, geometric appearance that scientists call euhedral.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">层楼高，足球场大小的晶体岩洞中，巨大的石膏岩（也称玄精石——译者注）晶体柱——世界上最大的独立晶体——杂乱无章地由岩洞的顶部、地面和岩壁出生发出来。尽管相互独立，这些晶体的外观并非毫无规律，它们突变出尖锐的具有几何形的外表，科学家称之为自形。</span></p> <blockquote>This jewel-like effect makes the giant crystals truly unique, according to John Rakovan, a mineralogist at Miami University in Ohio, who was not involved in the project.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; John Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">指出，珠宝样的外观赋予了这些巨大的晶体以绝对的独特性。他是俄亥俄州迈阿密大学的矿物学家，并没有加入这个研究项目。</span></p> <blockquote>\"When crystals get larger and larger, they become less euhedral, typically\"—and more rocklike. \"Scientists didn't think it was possible to get large crystals that are so morphologically perfect\" before the Cave of Crystals discovery, Rakovan said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;“随着晶体越长越大，它们的自形性会逐渐减弱，一般都是这样”——更像是岩石。在发现这个晶体岩洞之前“科学家们认为巨大的晶体不可能具有如此完美的形态”在，</span><span>Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>The translucent columns also resemble giant pillars of ice but are warmed by superheated air leaking up from underground magma chambers.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这些剔透的柱体就像巨大的冰柱，但又被过热的空气熔化，这些空气来自地下的岩浆房。</span></p> <blockquote>The combination of 90 percent humidity and a temperature of 118 degrees Fahrenheit (48 degrees Celsius) inside the cave can kill an unprepared human in just 30 minutes.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 在洞穴的内部，在</span><span>90%</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">湿度和华氏</span><span>118</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">度（</span><span>4</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;\">8</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;\">℃</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">）高温的共同作用下，毫无防备的人进入，将在</span><span>30</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分钟内死亡。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's a terrible and magical environment all at the same time,\" said Penelope Boston, an astrobiologist and cave scientist who appears in the new documentary Into the Lost Crystal Caves, which airs Sunday at 8 p.m. ET/PT on the National Geographic Channel. (The National Geographic Channel is part-owned by the National Geographic Society, which owns National Geographic News.)</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “这是一个恐怖的环境，但同时它又是神奇的，”</span><span>Penelope Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他是一位宇宙生物学家和洞穴科学家。此人在新节目“走进迷失的晶体洞穴”中露过面，这个节目在国家地理频道每周日晚</span><span>8</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">点</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">播送。（国家地理学会拥有国家地理频道的一部分，它同时还负责国家地理新闻。）</span></p> <blockquote>Beyond the Cave of Crystals</blockquote> <p><strong>晶体洞穴之上</strong></p> <blockquote>Discovered by miners in 2000, the Cave of Crystals is just one chamber in what appears to be a network of subterranean caverns beneath Naica—some well known and evocatively named: the Cave of Swords, the Queen's Eye, the Cave of Sails.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2000</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年被矿工发现时，晶体洞穴还仅仅是奈卡山脉地下洞穴系统的其中之一——其中的一些十分著名且有上口的名字：剑之洞，女王之眼，以及蜗牛洞。</span></p> <blockquote>In 2009 a video camera attached to a drill bit found hints of one more crystal-lined cave during the creation of the Robin Hole, a 2,000-foot-deep (600-meter-deep) ventilation shaft meant to cool mining tunnels below.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>,</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">安装在钻头上的摄像机捕捉到了又一个遍布晶体的洞穴的存迹，它正处于罗宾洞的形成时期，这是一个</span><span>2,000</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">英尺深的通风井，对冷却下面的矿道起着重要的作用。</span></p> <blockquote>Descending into the hole months later, in December 2009, a scientific team confirmed the new, naturally dry crystal cave about 500 feet (150 meters) below the surface.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 数月之后的</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>12</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">月，一个科考队深入了这个洞穴，他们确认这是一个新的自然风干形成的晶体洞穴，位于大约</span><span>500</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">英尺</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">（</span><span>150</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">米</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">）的地下。</span></p> <blockquote>Dubbed the Ice Palace, the new cave lacks giant pillars, but sparkles with rare crystal formations, including minerals resembling cauliflower and fiber-optic-like filaments.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管被称为水晶宫，这个新发现的洞穴缺少巨大的支柱，但是有趣的是它具有罕见的晶体构成，包括类似花椰菜的矿物和光线样的丝状物。</span></p> <blockquote>The mysteries of the Ice Palace will likely remain unsolved, however. The Industrias Peñoles mining company has decided to cover the Robin Hole and has also hinted that it may shut down the expensive water pumps that keep the Cave of Crystals dry, according to the documentary.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 然而，水晶宫的奥秘仍待解决。</span><span>Industrias Peñoles</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">矿业公司已经决定封存罗宾洞，并且暗示，可能关停昂贵的水泵。根据文件资料，该水泵原来是用于保持水晶洞干燥的。</span></p> <blockquote>\"I don't think they'll ever be able to preserve those caves,\" Miami University's Rakovan said. \"It'll be economically unfeasible.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我认为他们没有能力保存那些洞穴，”迈阿密大学的</span><span>Rakovan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“这在经济上是不可行的。”</span></p> <blockquote>But shutting down the caves isn't necessarily a bad thing, Rakovan added. \"It might actually preserve the crystals. And if at a later date it becomes important to get in there again, they could repump.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 但是关停洞穴并不是十分必要的坏事，</span><span>Rakobvan</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">补充道。“实际上，它可能保存住晶体。而且一旦日后需要再次进入洞穴，他们就得重新起泵。”</span></p> <blockquote>Ice-Cooled Suits Required</blockquote> <p><strong>进入洞穴需要制冷服</strong></p> <blockquote>Exploring the Naica caves requires more than just industrial strength water pumps. Scientists entering the complex in 2008 and 2009 wore custom-made, 45-pound (25-kilograms) cooling suits that extend mission times from 15 minutes to an hour.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 进入奈卡洞穴探险需要除工业用水泵外更多的防护。在</span><span>2008</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">和</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年间，科学家们进入这些复杂的洞穴系统是穿着制冷服的，这种服装是当地生产的，重达</span><span>45</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">磅</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">（</span><span>25</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">公斤</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">），能够将任务时间由</span><span>15</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分钟延长至</span><span>1</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时。</span></p> <blockquote>Each suit contains several ice-filled compartments as well as respirators connected to ice-filled backpacks, which send cool air to the wearer's lungs. Masks protect the eyes, which can scorch in the cave's heat.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 制冷服包含着若干由冰充满的部件，以及连在冰背囊上的人工呼吸机，它可以将冷却的空气传送至使用者的肺部。面罩则用来保护眼睛，眼睛在洞穴的高温下会被烤焦。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's funny, because when you look at the pictures of us in there in the suits, it looks like we're in an ice chamber, but it's just the reverse,\" said Boston, of the New Mexico Institute of Mining and Technology.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “这真有趣，因为当你看到我们穿着冷却服在洞里的照片，觉得好像我们是在一个冰冻的环境，但事实恰恰相反，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他来自矿物与科技的新墨西哥研究所。</span></p> <blockquote>Even with the protective gear, the scientists often operated at the edge of safety.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 即使有保护装置，科学家们仍然常常是在危险的边缘进行工作。</span></p> <blockquote>Ontario, Canada-based astrophysicist Sara Poirier said, \"We all just kept pushing further and further [into the cave], so by the time you are heading back, you've pushed yourself beyond the limits that are safe\"—and that's with the gear operating properly.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 安大略，加拿大背景的天体物理学家</span><span>Sara Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，“我们都坚持不断向洞穴深处推进，所以当你回望时，你已经将自己推向了安全限度之外”——所谓安全限度就是正确地使用防护装置。</span></p> <blockquote>At least one piece of equipment offered little protection. The portable Ice Cube—a newly designed, air-cooled, transparent tent designed to allow for two-hour Naica-caves missions—never cooled down enough to bring overheated bodies back to safe levels.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 至少有一套设备能提供点儿防护。便携式冰箱——一种新研发的，可用于空气冷却的透明帐篷，可令科学家们在奈卡洞穴中工作</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时——奈卡洞穴自身不能冷却到足够低的温度来使过热的肌体恢复至安全的水平。</span></p> <blockquote>Microbial Mystery in Cave of Crystals</blockquote> <p><strong>晶体洞穴中的微生物奇迹</strong></p> <blockquote>Though the calling card of the horseshoe-shaped Cave of Crystals may be its massive mineral formations, some of its biggest surprises are literally microscopic.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管马蹄形水晶洞穴的标志物就是它宏伟的矿物结构，然而它最令人惊叹的地方却是显微水平的。</span></p> <blockquote>In 2008 a team of scientists, including New Mexico Tech's Boston, investigated the cave and found microbial life living in tiny air pockets in the crystals.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2008</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年，一个科考队的专家，包括新墨西哥研究所的</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">，调查了这个洞穴并在一个晶体中的气穴中发现存活着微生物。</span></p> <blockquote>In December 2009 Boston returned to the cave with another team. From pools of water that hadn't been present during her first trip, the scientists collected bacteria as well as viruses that prey on the bacteria—something that was suspected but had not been confirmed on the first expedition.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年</span><span>12</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">月</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">与另一组科考队重返洞穴。在一湾第一次未曾发现的水中科学家们发现了细菌以及寄生于细菌的病毒——在第一次探险中怀疑存在这些生物，但当时并未确认。</span></p> <blockquote>Viruses, after all, are among the \"primary predators of bacteria,\" explained Danielle Winget, a biologist at the University of British Columbia, in the new documentary.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 病毒，归根结底，属于“细菌的初级捕食者，”</span><span>Danielle Winget</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">在一份新文献中解释道，他是英属哥伦比亚大学的生物学家。</span></p> <blockquote>Sure enough, the team found as many as 200 million viruses in a single drop of Cave of Crystals water.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 的确，科考队发现，在晶体岩洞的一滴水中包含着</span><span>2</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">亿个病毒。</span></p> <blockquote>But the virus finding was perhaps not the expedition's most surprising microbial discovery. Analysis of bacterial DNA from the Cave of Crystals showed that the tiny life-forms are related to microbes living in other extreme environments around the world, including caves in South Africa and Australia as well as hydrothermal vents (video).</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 但是，也许病毒的发现并不是此次探险中最令人惊讶的微生物发现。对晶体岩洞中的细菌的</span><span>DNA</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">分析显示这些微小的生命形式与在世界上的另外一些极端微生物相关，它们生存环境包括南非的岩洞和澳大利亚的热泉口。</span></p> <blockquote>\"We're picking up these patterns of similarities in places that are geographically widely separated,\" Boston said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我们在地理上广泛分布的很多地点都提取到了这些相似的模式，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>That similarity and separation adds up to a mystery, according to Curtis Suttle, a biologist at University of British Columbia and a member of the 2009 Cave of Crystals expedition.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 这些相似性与分离性共同造就了如此的神秘，</span><span>Curtis Suttle</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，他是英属哥伦比亚大学的生物学家，同时也是</span><span>2009</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">年水晶洞穴科考队的成员之一。</span></p> <blockquote>\"We don't really understand how it is that the organisms in a hydrothermal vent in Greece or a deep gold mine in South Africa are related to organisms that we find in a subsurface cave\" at Naica, Suttle said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我们并不真正的明白在希腊热泉口或者南非深邃金矿处的生物是如何与我们在奈卡发现的地下洞穴的生物产生关联的”</span><span>Suttle</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>\"It's hard to imagine some kind of underground [network] connecting South Africa with Mexico.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “很难想象在南非和墨西哥之间存在着地下网络的联系。”</span></p> <blockquote>Alien Underworlds</blockquote> <p><strong>外来的地下世界</strong></p> <blockquote>As mind-boggling as the idea of a possibly globe-spanning, underground bacterial network may be, some scientists see potential links between the Cave of Crystals and even farther-flung hot spots—for example, extreme environments on Mars and other worlds.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 有这样一个令人难以置信的观点，认为可能存在着全球范围的地下细菌网络，一些科学家看到了晶体洞穴和更加热门的领域的潜在联系——例如，在火星和其他星球上的极端环境。</span></p> <blockquote>Though Martian geology might be more static overall than Earth's, \"there may be residual pockets of geothermal activity that could provide a zone where water could be liquid and where chemically reduced gases from below can percolate up and act as a nutrient source,\" as in the Cave of Crystals, Boston said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 尽管火星的地质状况整体上比地球稳定，“仍可能存在地热活动的残留穴，可能提供一个使水保持液态的区域，使得地下的化学还原性气体能够渗出并起到晶体洞穴中氮源的作用，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。</span></p> <blockquote>Poirier, the Ontario astrophysicist, agreed.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">，安大略的天体物理学家，也同意这个观点。</span></p> <blockquote>\"For Mars, our best bet of finding life is to look underground,\" Poirier said. \"So there are a lot of parallels between humans exploring subterranean caves looking for microbes and Martian exploration in the future.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “对于火星，我们最有把握找到生命的地方是地下，”</span><span>Poirier</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“人们做了大量相似的工作去探索地下洞穴以及将来对火星的探索，以期发现微生物。”</span></p> <blockquote>If the caves on Mars are anything like the caverns beneath Naica mountain, she said, future Martian explorers will have to be trained to ignore the strange sights surrounding them.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 如果火星上的洞穴与奈卡山脉下的洞穴有些许相似，她说，未来的火星探险者就得学着无视他们周围奇妙的景观。</span></p> <blockquote>\"When you're in the caves, you're overwhelmed by the [harsh] conditions, but you're also overwhelmed by the beauty, and it's really hard to maintain your focus,\" she said.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “当你身处洞穴，恶劣的环境条件会令你不知所措，但同时你又会被它的美丽深深折服，这使得你很难集中注意力，”她说。</span></p> <blockquote>Even if scalding water submerges that beauty tomorrow, Boston said, the caves' scientific potential should live on, thanks to the multitude of samples already collected.</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 即使有朝一日沸水淹没了这美丽的景观，</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说，洞穴的学术潜力也将持续存在下去，因为我们已经收集了大量的样品。</span></p> <blockquote>\"My usual rule of thumb is for every hour you spend in the field, you spend at least a thousand hours on analysis,\" Boston said. \"So we've got our hands full.\"</blockquote> <p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “我的经验是，如果你采样花了</span><span>1</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">小时，那么你将花费上千倍的时间来分析它，”</span><span>Boston</span><span style=\"font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:'times new roman';mso-hansi-font-family:'times new roman';\">说。“所以我们的任务很重。”</span></p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190?from=rss_related\">重返水晶宫</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/141464?from=rss_related\">珊瑚美景</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/lost/141674?from=rss_related\">卫报图说－－本周野生动物图集</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/38018/137545?from=rss_related\">机场之最：奇异、古怪、可怕</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/173183/134103?from=rss_related\">【图集】18座最奇特的人工岛</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804571/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804571/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804571/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>") (pubDate nil "Tue, 12 Oct 2010 13:41:27 +0800") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142283") (dc:creator nil "Billie W") (fs:srclink nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283") (fs:srcfeed nil "http://www.yeeyan.org/feed/category/310") (fs:itemid nil "feedsky/yeeyan-science/~8024232/422804571/5034837"))) ("十种恐怖的巨型蜘蛛" "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.fr.msn.com/ecologie/photo/galerie.aspx?cp-documentid=150477936\">Les araignées les plus impressionnantes</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/83782\">陈庆凯</a></p><p><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/20/CA6453AA943603A2A8850B9E08F77.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\">蜘蛛是种让人不可小视的动物，这种最长可达30厘米的小型爬虫，遍及地球的每个角落，无畏地守护着自己的领地。凭借着八条长长的腿和出色的视力，蜘蛛是出色的捕食者，他们总能吃到新鲜的活猎物。不论对人类危险与否，蜘蛛总是让你浑身不自在。下面向您介绍几种巨型蜘蛛。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\">蟹蛛</h1> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/53/A62E897AED4127219D6D73B3AB3D60.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </span></p> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:18px;\">因其可以像螃蟹一样横行，故而得名蟹蛛。这是一种花丛里的蜘蛛，它们不结网，只是隐藏在花瓣中、静静候猎物的到来。蟹蛛没有尖刺或毒针，因此对人类没有危险。要注意的是，不要把蟹蛛（</span></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">&nbsp;l’araignée crabe</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">）和蜘蛛蟹（</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">le crabe araignée，又叫</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">araignée de mer japonaise</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">）混淆，后者可是名副其实的怪物，包含腿可以长达4米，但其实它是甲壳类动物。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\">黑寡妇蜘蛛</h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/5B/86CF48E631C404759C6BF3D078ED.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">切莫小瞧它那不足1.5CM的躯体，黑寡妇蜘蛛是世界最危险的蜘蛛。它的毒液毒性非常强，被叮咬后，猎物会恶心、痉挛、产生幻觉，直至死亡。交配时，雌蛛会将雄蛛全部吞噬，或是吞噬一部分。现实中，许多蜘蛛都会这么做，但是像黑寡妇一样吞噬自己性伴侣的例子并不多。</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">红腿蟏蛸（喜蛛）</span></font></h1> <div style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/E2/62C5B7218150C4D87492EC5A2EA1F1.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </font></div> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:'sans serif', tahoma, verdana, helvetica;line-height:21px;font-size:14px;\">红腿蟏蛸那长长的脚使它可以织出世界上最结实、最漂亮的网，丝线闪闪放光。它们是耐心的狩猎者，在网中等待猎物的到来，然后将其吃掉。它们对人类没有任何威胁。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">山猫蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/9D/533501C5848F1845D2CC3BDBBEF65.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">绿色、灰色或是黄褐色的山猫蜘蛛很容易屈身于植物丛中不被发现，它们用后腿前进，前腿平时抬起以便在捕猎时弹跳突袭猎物。它们危险性较低、不爱攻击人类，但是最好还是不要招惹它们。如果你把山猫蜘蛛惹毛了，它会狠狠狠跳到你的脸上……</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">巨人蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/FB/C83AE1E3F615B25FF5CB85F65F1.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">这是一种凶猛的捕鸟蛛。巨人蛛是世界上最大的蜘蛛，体长可达30厘米。它们夜间外出捕猎，小型的鸟类、爬虫、哺乳动物都可以成为它们的美餐。它的毒液不致命，而且即使它们杀死了人类，也并不食用人的尸体。</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">金属蓝蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/30/55F2D851848B711E3F65D9FDC94B6.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">通体深蓝色的金属蓝蛛让蜘蛛收藏者趋之若鹜。这种起源于亚洲的蜘蛛攻击性极强，而且被其叮咬十分痛苦。你饿可以在玻璃钢外观赏这种蜘蛛，最好不要蛋疼地接近它。</span></span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">红脚蜘蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C3/6D866ABE97A6ECF38DBC44DFBAB6.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">通体黑色反射红光，脚是玫瑰红色——这是这种无攻击性蜘蛛的明显特征。红脚蜘蛛喜欢群居，是唯一一种群居而不会相食的蜘蛛。它们没有毒液，你可以放心地用手爱抚它们。不要犹豫了，它们是作宠物蜘蛛的不二之选。</span></span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#669933\">烈阳巴布</font></font></font></h1> <div style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C2/3D2988E90B9E1168966DE41F19B.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </font></font></div> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">如果金属蓝蛛一样，烈阳巴布同业深受收藏者喜爱，它的毒液并不会致人死地，它们只以昆虫为食。烈阳巴布那八条黄色的毛茸茸的长脚让人为之震惊。</span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">狼蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C9/2E507DB6153DEE2CF897087D963BC.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">狼蛛白天藏匿、夜间捕食，</span></span></font></font><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:21px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;躯体从3毫米到3厘米不等，它们无所畏惧。狼蛛不害怕人类，如果你在它的领地逗留过久，它会追逐你。狼蛛的毒液虽不致命，却会引起组织坏死，因此被狼蛛叮咬极其痛苦，且伤口会留下疤痕。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">横纹金蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/CE/8164033643069351EFAF2CF498587.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">横纹金蛛是懂得易容术的狩猎者，它们黄黑相间的伪装色使其看起来像一只不起眼的黄蜂。横纹金蛛食量惊人，每天甚至可以吃掉四只蝗虫。它们同样对人类无害。</span></span></font></font></p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/103382/107917?from=rss_related\">生物的执念</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/49269/99465?from=rss_related\">多足机械奇迹：蜘蛛机器人</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/128539/94645?from=rss_related\">破解天然丝秘密，制造更强韧合成材料</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/125036/91856?from=rss_related\">天生的？害怕蜘蛛在你出生前就开始了？| 生活科学LiveScience</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/korchagin/71455?from=rss_related\">图片：微型多彩的“孔雀”蛛-每日电讯报</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804669/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804669/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804669/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166" (19635 51692) old 5 nil nil ((title nil "十种恐怖的巨型蜘蛛") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T02:37:32+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T02:37:32+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T02:37:32+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142166") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "陈庆凯") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/83782")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.fr.msn.com/ecologie/photo/galerie.aspx?cp-documentid=150477936\">Les araignées les plus impressionnantes</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/83782\">陈庆凯</a></p><p><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/20/CA6453AA943603A2A8850B9E08F77.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\">蜘蛛是种让人不可小视的动物，这种最长可达30厘米的小型爬虫，遍及地球的每个角落，无畏地守护着自己的领地。凭借着八条长长的腿和出色的视力，蜘蛛是出色的捕食者，他们总能吃到新鲜的活猎物。不论对人类危险与否，蜘蛛总是让你浑身不自在。下面向您介绍几种巨型蜘蛛。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\">蟹蛛</h1> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/53/A62E897AED4127219D6D73B3AB3D60.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </span></p> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:18px;\">因其可以像螃蟹一样横行，故而得名蟹蛛。这是一种花丛里的蜘蛛，它们不结网，只是隐藏在花瓣中、静静候猎物的到来。蟹蛛没有尖刺或毒针，因此对人类没有危险。要注意的是，不要把蟹蛛（</span></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">&nbsp;l’araignée crabe</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">）和蜘蛛蟹（</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">le crabe araignée，又叫</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">araignée de mer japonaise</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">）混淆，后者可是名副其实的怪物，包含腿可以长达4米，但其实它是甲壳类动物。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\">黑寡妇蜘蛛</h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/5B/86CF48E631C404759C6BF3D078ED.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">切莫小瞧它那不足1.5CM的躯体，黑寡妇蜘蛛是世界最危险的蜘蛛。它的毒液毒性非常强，被叮咬后，猎物会恶心、痉挛、产生幻觉，直至死亡。交配时，雌蛛会将雄蛛全部吞噬，或是吞噬一部分。现实中，许多蜘蛛都会这么做，但是像黑寡妇一样吞噬自己性伴侣的例子并不多。</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">红腿蟏蛸（喜蛛）</span></font></h1> <div style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/E2/62C5B7218150C4D87492EC5A2EA1F1.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </font></div> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:'sans serif', tahoma, verdana, helvetica;line-height:21px;font-size:14px;\">红腿蟏蛸那长长的脚使它可以织出世界上最结实、最漂亮的网，丝线闪闪放光。它们是耐心的狩猎者，在网中等待猎物的到来，然后将其吃掉。它们对人类没有任何威胁。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">山猫蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/9D/533501C5848F1845D2CC3BDBBEF65.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">绿色、灰色或是黄褐色的山猫蜘蛛很容易屈身于植物丛中不被发现，它们用后腿前进，前腿平时抬起以便在捕猎时弹跳突袭猎物。它们危险性较低、不爱攻击人类，但是最好还是不要招惹它们。如果你把山猫蜘蛛惹毛了，它会狠狠狠跳到你的脸上……</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">巨人蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/FB/C83AE1E3F615B25FF5CB85F65F1.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">这是一种凶猛的捕鸟蛛。巨人蛛是世界上最大的蜘蛛，体长可达30厘米。它们夜间外出捕猎，小型的鸟类、爬虫、哺乳动物都可以成为它们的美餐。它的毒液不致命，而且即使它们杀死了人类，也并不食用人的尸体。</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">金属蓝蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/30/55F2D851848B711E3F65D9FDC94B6.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">通体深蓝色的金属蓝蛛让蜘蛛收藏者趋之若鹜。这种起源于亚洲的蜘蛛攻击性极强，而且被其叮咬十分痛苦。你饿可以在玻璃钢外观赏这种蜘蛛，最好不要蛋疼地接近它。</span></span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">红脚蜘蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C3/6D866ABE97A6ECF38DBC44DFBAB6.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">通体黑色反射红光，脚是玫瑰红色——这是这种无攻击性蜘蛛的明显特征。红脚蜘蛛喜欢群居，是唯一一种群居而不会相食的蜘蛛。它们没有毒液，你可以放心地用手爱抚它们。不要犹豫了，它们是作宠物蜘蛛的不二之选。</span></span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#669933\">烈阳巴布</font></font></font></h1> <div style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C2/3D2988E90B9E1168966DE41F19B.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </font></font></div> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">如果金属蓝蛛一样，烈阳巴布同业深受收藏者喜爱，它的毒液并不会致人死地，它们只以昆虫为食。烈阳巴布那八条黄色的毛茸茸的长脚让人为之震惊。</span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">狼蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C9/2E507DB6153DEE2CF897087D963BC.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">狼蛛白天藏匿、夜间捕食，</span></span></font></font><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:21px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;躯体从3毫米到3厘米不等，它们无所畏惧。狼蛛不害怕人类，如果你在它的领地逗留过久，它会追逐你。狼蛛的毒液虽不致命，却会引起组织坏死，因此被狼蛛叮咬极其痛苦，且伤口会留下疤痕。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">横纹金蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/CE/8164033643069351EFAF2CF498587.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">横纹金蛛是懂得易容术的狩猎者，它们黄黑相间的伪装色使其看起来像一只不起眼的黄蜂。横纹金蛛食量惊人，每天甚至可以吃掉四只蝗虫。它们同样对人类无害。</span></span></font></font></p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/103382/107917?from=rss_related\">生物的执念</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/49269/99465?from=rss_related\">多足机械奇迹：蜘蛛机器人</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/128539/94645?from=rss_related\">破解天然丝秘密，制造更强韧合成材料</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/125036/91856?from=rss_related\">天生的？害怕蜘蛛在你出生前就开始了？| 生活科学LiveScience</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/korchagin/71455?from=rss_related\">图片：微型多彩的“孔雀”蛛&#45;每日电讯报</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.fr.msn.com/ecologie/photo/galerie.aspx?cp-documentid=150477936\">Les araignées les plus impressionnantes</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/83782\">陈庆凯</a></p><p><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/20/CA6453AA943603A2A8850B9E08F77.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\">蜘蛛是种让人不可小视的动物，这种最长可达30厘米的小型爬虫，遍及地球的每个角落，无畏地守护着自己的领地。凭借着八条长长的腿和出色的视力，蜘蛛是出色的捕食者，他们总能吃到新鲜的活猎物。不论对人类危险与否，蜘蛛总是让你浑身不自在。下面向您介绍几种巨型蜘蛛。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\">蟹蛛</h1> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/53/A62E897AED4127219D6D73B3AB3D60.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </span></p> <p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;font-size:14px;color:#333333;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:18px;\">因其可以像螃蟹一样横行，故而得名蟹蛛。这是一种花丛里的蜘蛛，它们不结网，只是隐藏在花瓣中、静静候猎物的到来。蟹蛛没有尖刺或毒针，因此对人类没有危险。要注意的是，不要把蟹蛛（</span></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">&nbsp;l’araignée crabe</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">）和蜘蛛蟹（</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">le crabe araignée，又叫</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">araignée de mer japonaise</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;color:#333333;\">）混淆，后者可是名副其实的怪物，包含腿可以长达4米，但其实它是甲壳类动物。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\">黑寡妇蜘蛛</h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/5B/86CF48E631C404759C6BF3D078ED.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">切莫小瞧它那不足1.5CM的躯体，黑寡妇蜘蛛是世界最危险的蜘蛛。它的毒液毒性非常强，被叮咬后，猎物会恶心、痉挛、产生幻觉，直至死亡。交配时，雌蛛会将雄蛛全部吞噬，或是吞噬一部分。现实中，许多蜘蛛都会这么做，但是像黑寡妇一样吞噬自己性伴侣的例子并不多。</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">红腿蟏蛸（喜蛛）</span></font></h1> <div style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/E2/62C5B7218150C4D87492EC5A2EA1F1.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </font></div> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:'sans serif', tahoma, verdana, helvetica;line-height:21px;font-size:14px;\">红腿蟏蛸那长长的脚使它可以织出世界上最结实、最漂亮的网，丝线闪闪放光。它们是耐心的狩猎者，在网中等待猎物的到来，然后将其吃掉。它们对人类没有任何威胁。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">山猫蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/9D/533501C5848F1845D2CC3BDBBEF65.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">绿色、灰色或是黄褐色的山猫蜘蛛很容易屈身于植物丛中不被发现，它们用后腿前进，前腿平时抬起以便在捕猎时弹跳突袭猎物。它们危险性较低、不爱攻击人类，但是最好还是不要招惹它们。如果你把山猫蜘蛛惹毛了，它会狠狠狠跳到你的脸上……</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">巨人蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/FB/C83AE1E3F615B25FF5CB85F65F1.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></p> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">这是一种凶猛的捕鸟蛛。巨人蛛是世界上最大的蜘蛛，体长可达30厘米。它们夜间外出捕猎，小型的鸟类、爬虫、哺乳动物都可以成为它们的美餐。它的毒液不致命，而且即使它们杀死了人类，也并不食用人的尸体。</span></span></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">金属蓝蜘蛛</span></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/30/55F2D851848B711E3F65D9FDC94B6.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">通体深蓝色的金属蓝蛛让蜘蛛收藏者趋之若鹜。这种起源于亚洲的蜘蛛攻击性极强，而且被其叮咬十分痛苦。你饿可以在玻璃钢外观赏这种蜘蛛，最好不要蛋疼地接近它。</span></span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">红脚蜘蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C3/6D866ABE97A6ECF38DBC44DFBAB6.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">通体黑色反射红光，脚是玫瑰红色——这是这种无攻击性蜘蛛的明显特征。红脚蜘蛛喜欢群居，是唯一一种群居而不会相食的蜘蛛。它们没有毒液，你可以放心地用手爱抚它们。不要犹豫了，它们是作宠物蜘蛛的不二之选。</span></span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#669933\">烈阳巴布</font></font></font></h1> <div style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C2/3D2988E90B9E1168966DE41F19B.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </font></font></div> <p style=\"font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:14px;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">如果金属蓝蛛一样，烈阳巴布同业深受收藏者喜爱，它的毒液并不会致人死地，它们只以昆虫为食。烈阳巴布那八条黄色的毛茸茸的长脚让人为之震惊。</span></font></font></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">狼蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/C9/2E507DB6153DEE2CF897087D963BC.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">狼蛛白天藏匿、夜间捕食，</span></span></font></font><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:21px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;躯体从3毫米到3厘米不等，它们无所畏惧。狼蛛不害怕人类，如果你在它的领地逗留过久，它会追逐你。狼蛛的毒液虽不致命，却会引起组织坏死，因此被狼蛛叮咬极其痛苦，且伤口会留下疤痕。</span></p> <h1 style=\"font-size:34px;margin-top:15px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:6px;padding-left:0px;background-color:transparent;color:#669933;font-family:tahoma, sans-serif;font-weight:normal;line-height:1em;\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color:#669933;\">横纹金蛛</span></font></font></h1> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><img src=\"http://estb.msn.com/i/CE/8164033643069351EFAF2CF498587.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></span></font></font></p> <p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" color=\"#333333\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"tahoma, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"line-height:14px;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family:tahoma;line-height:18px;font-size:14px;\">横纹金蛛是懂得易容术的狩猎者，它们黄黑相间的伪装色使其看起来像一只不起眼的黄蜂。横纹金蛛食量惊人，每天甚至可以吃掉四只蝗虫。它们同样对人类无害。</span></span></font></font></p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/103382/107917?from=rss_related\">生物的执念</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/49269/99465?from=rss_related\">多足机械奇迹：蜘蛛机器人</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/128539/94645?from=rss_related\">破解天然丝秘密，制造更强韧合成材料</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/125036/91856?from=rss_related\">天生的？害怕蜘蛛在你出生前就开始了？| 生活科学LiveScience</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/korchagin/71455?from=rss_related\">图片：微型多彩的“孔雀”蛛&#45;每日电讯报</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422804669/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804669/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422804669/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>") (pubDate nil "Tue, 12 Oct 2010 10:37:32 +0800") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142166") (dc:creator nil "陈庆凯") (fs:srclink nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/83782/142166") (fs:srcfeed nil "http://www.yeeyan.org/feed/category/310") (fs:itemid nil "feedsky/yeeyan-science/~8024232/422804669/5034837"))) ("动物也爱爱" "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences-technologies/2010/07/30/01030-20100730DIMWWW00471-les-codes-de-lamour-chez-les-animaux.php\">Les codes de l’amour chez les animaux</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/168781\">SIRENE</a></p><blockquote>Les codes de l’amour chez les animaux</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> 动物也爱爱</strong></p> <blockquote>EN IMAGES - Pour une nuit ou pour la vie, l'été ouvre la saison des parades amoureuses et de la reproduction pour de nombreuses espèces animales. L'occasion de lever le voile sur l'intimité des amours sauvages et d'éclairer les alcôves de nos amies les bêtes.</blockquote> <p>图片展示—— 一晚或终生，夏季拉开了众多种类动物的炫耀求偶及繁殖的序幕。现在是个好机会，一起来看看我们的朋友——野生动物间亲密的情爱和“私生活”吧！</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081046_22046.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Parvenu à ses fins, le roi des animaux semble tout à son plaisir. Un moment hors du temps que ne partage pas du tout la lionne. Comme tous les félins, le lion fait souvent souffrir sa compagne. (Mitsuaki Iwago/Minden Pictures)</blockquote> <p>“完胜”！这头兽中之王看起来完全沉浸在喜悦之中。母狮却完全没有分享。跟所有的猫科动物一样，雄狮常常 “弄疼” 他的 “女伴”。（Mitsuaki Iwago/Minden Pictures)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081043_19885.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Chez les oiseaux, comme ici chez les martins-pêcheurs, l’accouplement est bref et intense, alors que les manoeuvres d’approche peuvent durer des heures. (Ben Van Den Brink/Foto Natura/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>在鸟类种族，就像这对翠鸟，交配短促而激烈，但是“表达爱意”的过程可持续数小时。（Ben Van Den Brink/Foto Natura/Minden Pictures.J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081024_26315.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Tendresse ou comportement programmé ? Seule certitude, les seiches s’accouplent après des parades spectaculaires. (Fred Bavendam/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>是温情还是“刻意”的行为？可以肯定的是，墨鱼是在蔚为壮观的炫耀求偶行为之后开始交配。（Fred Bavendam/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081033_17265.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les bonobos ont des comportements très proches de ceux des humains. (Frans Lanting/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;(产于非洲刚果河以南的)倭黑猩猩 。不得不说，他们的“姿势”也有点儿太像人类了！（Frans Lanting/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081026_76056.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Pour parvenir à ses fins, le grizzly a affronté de nombreux prétendants, puis a séduit sa femelle en lui mordillant le cou et en grognant. (Yva Momatiuk & John Eastcott/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>为了成功求偶，（产于美洲的）大褐熊在“ 迎战 \" 了数名“ 觊觎者 ”之后，来向母熊“求爱”，他发出低沉的声音，在她脖子上轻轻咬。（Yva Momatiuk &John Eastcott/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081003_37574.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>L’éléphant n’a, en moyenne, qu’un rapport sexuel tous les cinq ans. La période de gestation des femelles dure plus de deux ans. (C) Art Wolfe/Art Wolfe Stock/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>大象平均每5年才有一次“性关系”。雌象的妊娠期长达两年多。(（C）Art Wolfe/Art Wolfe Stock/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081003_28780.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <blockquote>Chez de nombreuses espèces de batraciens, le mâle peut chevaucher la femelle pendant de longues heures. (James Christensen/ Foto Natura/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>在众多种类的两栖类动物里，雄性可以“骑”在雌性身上数小时。（James Christensen/Foto Natura/ Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081038_44509.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les insectes, ici des charançons de Nouvelle-Guinée, ont des comportements invariables. (Mark Moffett/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>昆虫，新几内亚象虫，总是同一“举止”。（Mark Moffett/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081011_14747.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les papillons ont parfois des moeurs homosexuelles. (Ingo Arndt/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>蝴蝶有时也“同性爱”。（Ingo Arndt/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081012_30625.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Soudées l’une à l’autre, ces punaises du Costa-Rica («Anisocelis flavolineata») peuvent rester ainsi toute une journée. (Michael & Patricia Fogden/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>“对接”在一起——哥斯达黎加蝽能够这样待一整天。（Michael &Patricia Fogden/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081045_76982.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Tout un symbole ! Chez les cygnes, la parade et l’accouplement ne sont que douceur. (Flip De Nooyer/ Foto Natura/Minden Pictures)</blockquote> <p>简直是模范！在天鹅的炫耀求偶及交配过程中，一切都是“温柔”，只有“温柔”。</p> <p>（Flip De Nooyer/ Foto Natura/Minden Picetures)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081012_20313.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Puissant et fébrile, le cerf peut briser l’échine de la biche sous ses assauts. Un accident qui, heureusement, reste rare. (Elliott Neep/ FLPA/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>强健而兴奋的雄鹿在“冲击”过程中有可能毁坏雌鹿的脊柱。万幸，这种“事故”还是很少发生。（Elliott Neep/ FLPA/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081046_85021.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Chez ces grillons d’Amérique («Cyphoderris strepitans»), la femelle dévore les ailes du mâle pendant l’accouplement. (Piotr Naskrecki/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>美洲蟋蟀。雌性蟋蟀在交配中吃掉雄性的翅膀。（Piotr Naskrecki /Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081027_73286.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Deux dauphins.de l'Atlantique. (Jonathan Bird/Peter Arnold/Biosphoto)</blockquote> <p>大西洋的两只海豚。（Jonathan Bird/Peter Arnold/ Biosphoto)</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/125722/141999?from=rss_related\">10/10/10：大喜结婚日，极客们的另类解读</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/lost/141674?from=rss_related\">卫报图说－－本周野生动物图集</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/79130/132003?from=rss_related\">等待</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/172111/140883?from=rss_related\">一个有趣的爱情故事——『那通电话』</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/179021/140003?from=rss_related\">我妈妈不会相信我真的是同志！</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422671729/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422671729/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422671729/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398" (19635 48830) old 6 nil nil ((title nil "动物也爱爱") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T01:49:50+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T01:49:50+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-12T01:49:50+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142398") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "SIRENE") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/168781")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences-technologies/2010/07/30/01030-20100730DIMWWW00471-les-codes-de-lamour-chez-les-animaux.php\">Les codes de l’amour chez les animaux</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/168781\">SIRENE</a></p><blockquote>Les codes de l’amour chez les animaux</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> 动物也爱爱</strong></p> <blockquote>EN IMAGES - Pour une nuit ou pour la vie, l'été ouvre la saison des parades amoureuses et de la reproduction pour de nombreuses espèces animales. L'occasion de lever le voile sur l'intimité des amours sauvages et d'éclairer les alcôves de nos amies les bêtes.</blockquote> <p>图片展示—— 一晚或终生，夏季拉开了众多种类动物的炫耀求偶及繁殖的序幕。现在是个好机会，一起来看看我们的朋友——野生动物间亲密的情爱和“私生活”吧！</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081046_22046.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Parvenu à ses fins, le roi des animaux semble tout à son plaisir. Un moment hors du temps que ne partage pas du tout la lionne. Comme tous les félins, le lion fait souvent souffrir sa compagne. (Mitsuaki Iwago/Minden Pictures)</blockquote> <p>“完胜”！这头兽中之王看起来完全沉浸在喜悦之中。母狮却完全没有分享。跟所有的猫科动物一样，雄狮常常 “弄疼” 他的 “女伴”。（Mitsuaki Iwago/Minden Pictures)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081043_19885.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Chez les oiseaux, comme ici chez les martins-pêcheurs, l’accouplement est bref et intense, alors que les manoeuvres d’approche peuvent durer des heures. (Ben Van Den Brink/Foto Natura/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>在鸟类种族，就像这对翠鸟，交配短促而激烈，但是“表达爱意”的过程可持续数小时。（Ben Van Den Brink/Foto Natura/Minden Pictures.J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081024_26315.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Tendresse ou comportement programmé ? Seule certitude, les seiches s’accouplent après des parades spectaculaires. (Fred Bavendam/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>是温情还是“刻意”的行为？可以肯定的是，墨鱼是在蔚为壮观的炫耀求偶行为之后开始交配。（Fred Bavendam/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081033_17265.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les bonobos ont des comportements très proches de ceux des humains. (Frans Lanting/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;(产于非洲刚果河以南的)倭黑猩猩 。不得不说，他们的“姿势”也有点儿太像人类了！（Frans Lanting/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081026_76056.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Pour parvenir à ses fins, le grizzly a affronté de nombreux prétendants, puis a séduit sa femelle en lui mordillant le cou et en grognant. (Yva Momatiuk & John Eastcott/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>为了成功求偶，（产于美洲的）大褐熊在“ 迎战 \" 了数名“ 觊觎者 ”之后，来向母熊“求爱”，他发出低沉的声音，在她脖子上轻轻咬。（Yva Momatiuk &John Eastcott/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081003_37574.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>L’éléphant n’a, en moyenne, qu’un rapport sexuel tous les cinq ans. La période de gestation des femelles dure plus de deux ans. (C) Art Wolfe/Art Wolfe Stock/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>大象平均每5年才有一次“性关系”。雌象的妊娠期长达两年多。(（C）Art Wolfe/Art Wolfe Stock/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081003_28780.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <blockquote>Chez de nombreuses espèces de batraciens, le mâle peut chevaucher la femelle pendant de longues heures. (James Christensen/ Foto Natura/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>在众多种类的两栖类动物里，雄性可以“骑”在雌性身上数小时。（James Christensen/Foto Natura/ Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081038_44509.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les insectes, ici des charançons de Nouvelle-Guinée, ont des comportements invariables. (Mark Moffett/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>昆虫，新几内亚象虫，总是同一“举止”。（Mark Moffett/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081011_14747.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les papillons ont parfois des moeurs homosexuelles. (Ingo Arndt/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>蝴蝶有时也“同性爱”。（Ingo Arndt/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081012_30625.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Soudées l’une à l’autre, ces punaises du Costa-Rica («Anisocelis flavolineata») peuvent rester ainsi toute une journée. (Michael & Patricia Fogden/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>“对接”在一起——哥斯达黎加蝽能够这样待一整天。（Michael &Patricia Fogden/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081045_76982.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Tout un symbole ! Chez les cygnes, la parade et l’accouplement ne sont que douceur. (Flip De Nooyer/ Foto Natura/Minden Pictures)</blockquote> <p>简直是模范！在天鹅的炫耀求偶及交配过程中，一切都是“温柔”，只有“温柔”。</p> <p>（Flip De Nooyer/ Foto Natura/Minden Picetures)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081012_20313.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Puissant et fébrile, le cerf peut briser l’échine de la biche sous ses assauts. Un accident qui, heureusement, reste rare. (Elliott Neep/ FLPA/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>强健而兴奋的雄鹿在“冲击”过程中有可能毁坏雌鹿的脊柱。万幸，这种“事故”还是很少发生。（Elliott Neep/ FLPA/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081046_85021.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Chez ces grillons d’Amérique («Cyphoderris strepitans»), la femelle dévore les ailes du mâle pendant l’accouplement. (Piotr Naskrecki/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>美洲蟋蟀。雌性蟋蟀在交配中吃掉雄性的翅膀。（Piotr Naskrecki /Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081027_73286.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Deux dauphins.de l'Atlantique. (Jonathan Bird/Peter Arnold/Biosphoto)</blockquote> <p>大西洋的两只海豚。（Jonathan Bird/Peter Arnold/ Biosphoto)</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/125722/141999?from=rss_related\">10/10/10：大喜结婚日，极客们的另类解读</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/lost/141674?from=rss_related\">卫报图说－－本周野生动物图集</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/79130/132003?from=rss_related\">等待</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/172111/140883?from=rss_related\">一个有趣的爱情故事——『那通电话』</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/179021/140003?from=rss_related\">我妈妈不会相信我真的是同志！</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences-technologies/2010/07/30/01030-20100730DIMWWW00471-les-codes-de-lamour-chez-les-animaux.php\">Les codes de l’amour chez les animaux</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/168781\">SIRENE</a></p><blockquote>Les codes de l’amour chez les animaux</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> 动物也爱爱</strong></p> <blockquote>EN IMAGES - Pour une nuit ou pour la vie, l'été ouvre la saison des parades amoureuses et de la reproduction pour de nombreuses espèces animales. L'occasion de lever le voile sur l'intimité des amours sauvages et d'éclairer les alcôves de nos amies les bêtes.</blockquote> <p>图片展示—— 一晚或终生，夏季拉开了众多种类动物的炫耀求偶及繁殖的序幕。现在是个好机会，一起来看看我们的朋友——野生动物间亲密的情爱和“私生活”吧！</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081046_22046.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Parvenu à ses fins, le roi des animaux semble tout à son plaisir. Un moment hors du temps que ne partage pas du tout la lionne. Comme tous les félins, le lion fait souvent souffrir sa compagne. (Mitsuaki Iwago/Minden Pictures)</blockquote> <p>“完胜”！这头兽中之王看起来完全沉浸在喜悦之中。母狮却完全没有分享。跟所有的猫科动物一样，雄狮常常 “弄疼” 他的 “女伴”。（Mitsuaki Iwago/Minden Pictures)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081043_19885.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Chez les oiseaux, comme ici chez les martins-pêcheurs, l’accouplement est bref et intense, alors que les manoeuvres d’approche peuvent durer des heures. (Ben Van Den Brink/Foto Natura/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>在鸟类种族，就像这对翠鸟，交配短促而激烈，但是“表达爱意”的过程可持续数小时。（Ben Van Den Brink/Foto Natura/Minden Pictures.J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081024_26315.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Tendresse ou comportement programmé ? Seule certitude, les seiches s’accouplent après des parades spectaculaires. (Fred Bavendam/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>是温情还是“刻意”的行为？可以肯定的是，墨鱼是在蔚为壮观的炫耀求偶行为之后开始交配。（Fred Bavendam/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081033_17265.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les bonobos ont des comportements très proches de ceux des humains. (Frans Lanting/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>&nbsp;(产于非洲刚果河以南的)倭黑猩猩 。不得不说，他们的“姿势”也有点儿太像人类了！（Frans Lanting/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081026_76056.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Pour parvenir à ses fins, le grizzly a affronté de nombreux prétendants, puis a séduit sa femelle en lui mordillant le cou et en grognant. (Yva Momatiuk & John Eastcott/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>为了成功求偶，（产于美洲的）大褐熊在“ 迎战 \" 了数名“ 觊觎者 ”之后，来向母熊“求爱”，他发出低沉的声音，在她脖子上轻轻咬。（Yva Momatiuk &John Eastcott/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081003_37574.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>L’éléphant n’a, en moyenne, qu’un rapport sexuel tous les cinq ans. La période de gestation des femelles dure plus de deux ans. (C) Art Wolfe/Art Wolfe Stock/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>大象平均每5年才有一次“性关系”。雌象的妊娠期长达两年多。(（C）Art Wolfe/Art Wolfe Stock/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081003_28780.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <blockquote>Chez de nombreuses espèces de batraciens, le mâle peut chevaucher la femelle pendant de longues heures. (James Christensen/ Foto Natura/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>在众多种类的两栖类动物里，雄性可以“骑”在雌性身上数小时。（James Christensen/Foto Natura/ Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081038_44509.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les insectes, ici des charançons de Nouvelle-Guinée, ont des comportements invariables. (Mark Moffett/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>昆虫，新几内亚象虫，总是同一“举止”。（Mark Moffett/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081011_14747.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Les papillons ont parfois des moeurs homosexuelles. (Ingo Arndt/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>蝴蝶有时也“同性爱”。（Ingo Arndt/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081012_30625.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Soudées l’une à l’autre, ces punaises du Costa-Rica («Anisocelis flavolineata») peuvent rester ainsi toute une journée. (Michael & Patricia Fogden/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>“对接”在一起——哥斯达黎加蝽能够这样待一整天。（Michael &Patricia Fogden/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081045_76982.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Tout un symbole ! Chez les cygnes, la parade et l’accouplement ne sont que douceur. (Flip De Nooyer/ Foto Natura/Minden Pictures)</blockquote> <p>简直是模范！在天鹅的炫耀求偶及交配过程中，一切都是“温柔”，只有“温柔”。</p> <p>（Flip De Nooyer/ Foto Natura/Minden Picetures)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081012_20313.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Puissant et fébrile, le cerf peut briser l’échine de la biche sous ses assauts. Un accident qui, heureusement, reste rare. (Elliott Neep/ FLPA/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>强健而兴奋的雄鹿在“冲击”过程中有可能毁坏雌鹿的脊柱。万幸，这种“事故”还是很少发生。（Elliott Neep/ FLPA/Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081046_85021.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Chez ces grillons d’Amérique («Cyphoderris strepitans»), la femelle dévore les ailes du mâle pendant l’accouplement. (Piotr Naskrecki/Minden Pictures/J.H. Editorial)</blockquote> <p>美洲蟋蟀。雌性蟋蟀在交配中吃掉雄性的翅膀。（Piotr Naskrecki /Minden Pictures/J.H.Editorial)</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.yeeyan.org/upload/attached/2010-10/12/20101012081027_73286.jpg\" border=\"0\" /></p> <blockquote>Deux dauphins.de l'Atlantique. (Jonathan Bird/Peter Arnold/Biosphoto)</blockquote> <p>大西洋的两只海豚。（Jonathan Bird/Peter Arnold/ Biosphoto)</p><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/125722/141999?from=rss_related\">10/10/10：大喜结婚日，极客们的另类解读</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/lost/141674?from=rss_related\">卫报图说－－本周野生动物图集</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/79130/132003?from=rss_related\">等待</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/172111/140883?from=rss_related\">一个有趣的爱情故事——『那通电话』</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/179021/140003?from=rss_related\">我妈妈不会相信我真的是同志！</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422671729/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422671729/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422671729/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>") (pubDate nil "Tue, 12 Oct 2010 09:49:50 +0800") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142398") (dc:creator nil "SIRENE") (fs:srclink nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/168781/142398") (fs:srcfeed nil "http://www.yeeyan.org/feed/category/310") (fs:itemid nil "feedsky/yeeyan-science/~8024232/422671729/5034837"))) ("重返水晶宫" "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/09/photogalleries/101008-giant-crystal-cave-science-mexico-pictures/\">Pictures: Return to the Crystal Caves</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/102975\">leonaries</a></p><div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-27_27283_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>地下水晶王国</div> <div>照片由&nbsp;Oscar Necoechea、 Speleoresearch 和 Films/NGT提供</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>2000年，在墨西哥的奈卡地区地下304米的深处，科学家们发现了一个水晶洞穴，身着橘红色制冷工作服的科学家们对这个洞穴进行了考察。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>“水晶宫”是一个布满罕见晶体块的洞穴。探险队分别于2008和2009年对这个宛如外行星的空间进行了探索，揭示了这里的生物学奥秘。在星期日面世的最新一期《国家地理》中，《深入失落的水晶洞穴》一文对此进行了详细的介绍。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>2010年10月8日出版</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-12_27277_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>矿物花园 </div> <div>在这张2009年12月拍摄的照片里，晶体“菜花”破土而出，生长在水晶宫的地面和屋顶上。新发现的水晶宫位于地下150米处，原来的水晶洞之上。</div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-22_27281_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>冰箱</div> <div>2009年，水晶洞里的一位探险队员正在冰箱（右）里乘凉。冰箱实际上是一个安装着空调、四面由塑料围起来的帐篷，可以让队员们在两个小时的任务里不受奈卡洞穴那致命的温度和湿度的伤害。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>在这个高温潮湿的洞穴里，便携式帐篷根本无法将队员们过热的体温降到安全线以下。</div> &nbsp;&nbsp;<div><br /> <img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-16_27278_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>石中剑</div> &nbsp;&nbsp;<div>亚瑟王的神剑正在水晶洞中缓缓升起。这块剑形的水晶散发着珠宝般的光芒，据迈阿密大学俄亥俄分校的矿物学家约翰·雷科凡说，在水晶洞外，人们从来都没有见过这样的水晶。 </div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-11_27276_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>丝水晶</div> <div>如同光纤一般的罕见水晶体正在水晶宫的地面上闪闪发光。<br /> <br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-21_27280_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>活物</div> <div>2009年12月，科学家佩内洛普·波士顿、迈克尔·斯派尔德和丹尼尔·韦恩盖特（由左及右）从水晶洞里的一个水洼中采集了样本。随后的实验室分析表明，在一滴这样的水中，存在着约2亿个病毒。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-26_27282_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>孤城</div> <div>三位穿着定制工作服的科学家正在水晶洞内考察。这种重达25公斤的制冷服可以将他们在洞内的停留时间由25分钟延长至1小时。</div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-23_27274_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>吹凉风</div> <div>科学家们正在水晶洞外一个地下营地里的制冷帐篷内休息。洞内的湿度为90%，温度高达48摄氏度。如果不带任何防护，一个人在洞内至多只能生存30分钟。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-28_27284_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>异乡异客</div> <div>如果不是因为使用工业水泵采掘洞内的银、锌、铅等矿物质，水晶洞将会一直泡在热水之中。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-20_27279_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>玻璃心</div> <div>科学家桑德拉·布里塞尼奥·普列托正在检查水晶洞内的石膏样本。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-29_27285_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>惊人情境</div> <div>在两层楼高、足球场那么大的水晶洞里，存在着大约一百多块巨型水晶。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283?from=rss_related\">别有洞天的水晶宫，出离美丽</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/142174?from=rss_related\">【设计图集】23款创意独特的鼠标设计</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/141728?from=rss_related\">【设计图集】妙不可言的雪花照片</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/141752?from=rss_related\">【设计图集】50种精美而高效的包装设计</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/142096?from=rss_related\">仍然不是所有人能享有互联网</a></p><img src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/t1/422471871/yeeyan-science/feedsky/s.gif?r=http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190\" border=\"0\" height=\"0\" width=\"0\" style=\"position:absolute\" /><p class=\"fswww1\"><a href=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/l/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422471871/art01.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img border=\"0\" ismap=\"ismap\" src=\"http://www1.feedsky.com/r/i/feedsky/yeeyan-science/422471871/art01.gif\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" /></a></p>" "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190" (19635 413) old 7 nil nil ((title nil "重返水晶宫") (link nil "http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190") (created ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-11T12:22:53+00:00") (issued ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-11T12:22:53+00:00") (modified ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "2010-10-11T12:22:53+00:00") (id ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) "tag:feed.yeeyan.org:translation/142190") (author ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom")) (name nil "leonaries") (uri nil "http://space.yeeyan.org/u/102975")) (content ((xmlns . "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom") (type . "html")) "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/09/photogalleries/101008-giant-crystal-cave-science-mexico-pictures/\">Pictures: Return to the Crystal Caves</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/102975\">leonaries</a></p><div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-27_27283_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>地下水晶王国</div> <div>照片由&nbsp;Oscar Necoechea、 Speleoresearch 和 Films/NGT提供</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>2000年，在墨西哥的奈卡地区地下304米的深处，科学家们发现了一个水晶洞穴，身着橘红色制冷工作服的科学家们对这个洞穴进行了考察。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>“水晶宫”是一个布满罕见晶体块的洞穴。探险队分别于2008和2009年对这个宛如外行星的空间进行了探索，揭示了这里的生物学奥秘。在星期日面世的最新一期《国家地理》中，《深入失落的水晶洞穴》一文对此进行了详细的介绍。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>2010年10月8日出版</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-12_27277_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>矿物花园 </div> <div>在这张2009年12月拍摄的照片里，晶体“菜花”破土而出，生长在水晶宫的地面和屋顶上。新发现的水晶宫位于地下150米处，原来的水晶洞之上。</div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-22_27281_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>冰箱</div> <div>2009年，水晶洞里的一位探险队员正在冰箱（右）里乘凉。冰箱实际上是一个安装着空调、四面由塑料围起来的帐篷，可以让队员们在两个小时的任务里不受奈卡洞穴那致命的温度和湿度的伤害。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>在这个高温潮湿的洞穴里，便携式帐篷根本无法将队员们过热的体温降到安全线以下。</div> &nbsp;&nbsp;<div><br /> <img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-16_27278_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>石中剑</div> &nbsp;&nbsp;<div>亚瑟王的神剑正在水晶洞中缓缓升起。这块剑形的水晶散发着珠宝般的光芒，据迈阿密大学俄亥俄分校的矿物学家约翰·雷科凡说，在水晶洞外，人们从来都没有见过这样的水晶。 </div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-11_27276_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>丝水晶</div> <div>如同光纤一般的罕见水晶体正在水晶宫的地面上闪闪发光。<br /> <br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-21_27280_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>活物</div> <div>2009年12月，科学家佩内洛普·波士顿、迈克尔·斯派尔德和丹尼尔·韦恩盖特（由左及右）从水晶洞里的一个水洼中采集了样本。随后的实验室分析表明，在一滴这样的水中，存在着约2亿个病毒。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-26_27282_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>孤城</div> <div>三位穿着定制工作服的科学家正在水晶洞内考察。这种重达25公斤的制冷服可以将他们在洞内的停留时间由25分钟延长至1小时。</div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-23_27274_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>吹凉风</div> <div>科学家们正在水晶洞外一个地下营地里的制冷帐篷内休息。洞内的湿度为90%，温度高达48摄氏度。如果不带任何防护，一个人在洞内至多只能生存30分钟。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-28_27284_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>异乡异客</div> <div>如果不是因为使用工业水泵采掘洞内的银、锌、铅等矿物质，水晶洞将会一直泡在热水之中。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-20_27279_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>玻璃心</div> <div>科学家桑德拉·布里塞尼奥·普列托正在检查水晶洞内的石膏样本。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-29_27285_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>惊人情境</div> <div>在两层楼高、足球场那么大的水晶洞里，存在着大约一百多块巨型水晶。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div><p><a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/102975/142190#newComment\">添加新评论</a></p><p><strong>相关文章：</strong></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/174944/142283?from=rss_related\">别有洞天的水晶宫，出离美丽</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/142174?from=rss_related\">【设计图集】23款创意独特的鼠标设计</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/141728?from=rss_related\">【设计图集】妙不可言的雪花照片</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/141752?from=rss_related\">【设计图集】50种精美而高效的包装设计</a></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://article.yeeyan.org/view/163202/142096?from=rss_related\">仍然不是所有人能享有互联网</a></p>") (content:encoded nil "<p>原作者：<br />来源<a href=\"http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/09/photogalleries/101008-giant-crystal-cave-science-mexico-pictures/\">Pictures: Return to the Crystal Caves</a><br/>译者<a href=\"http://space.yeeyan.org/u/102975\">leonaries</a></p><div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-27_27283_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>地下水晶王国</div> <div>照片由&nbsp;Oscar Necoechea、 Speleoresearch 和 Films/NGT提供</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>2000年，在墨西哥的奈卡地区地下304米的深处，科学家们发现了一个水晶洞穴，身着橘红色制冷工作服的科学家们对这个洞穴进行了考察。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>“水晶宫”是一个布满罕见晶体块的洞穴。探险队分别于2008和2009年对这个宛如外行星的空间进行了探索，揭示了这里的生物学奥秘。在星期日面世的最新一期《国家地理》中，《深入失落的水晶洞穴》一文对此进行了详细的介绍。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>2010年10月8日出版</div> <div><br /> </div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-12_27277_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div><br /> </div> <div>矿物花园 </div> <div>在这张2009年12月拍摄的照片里，晶体“菜花”破土而出，生长在水晶宫的地面和屋顶上。新发现的水晶宫位于地下150米处，原来的水晶洞之上。</div> <div><img src=\"http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/272/cache/return-crystal-caves-22_27281_600x450.jpg\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /><br /> </div> <div>冰箱</div> <div>2009年，水晶洞里的一位探险队员正在冰箱（右）里乘凉。冰箱实际上是一个安装着空调、四面由塑料围起来的帐篷，可以让队员们在两个小时的任务里不受奈卡洞穴那致命的温度和湿度的伤害。</div> <div><br /> </div> <div>在这个高温潮湿的洞穴里，便携式帐篷根本无法将队员们过热的体温降到安全线以下。</